animal.description:
Pascal is a 2-3 year old male red merle Australian Shepherd. Originally found as a stray, he has been fully vetted and has adjusted well to being a loving family pet in his foster home.  He is housebroken, crate trained (as long as there is a bed in his crate), neutered, HW- and current on immunizations.

Pascal is great with other dog but not cats.  He loves to play with his humans and other dogs.  He is full of energy and needs humans who are equally as active. 

He is on medication to regulate and control a skin disorder and his coat is coming in beautifully.

If you think that Pascal is the perfect fit for your family, please fill out our application:

https://www.australianshepherdsfurever.org/adoption-application

All adoption fees are used for future rescue efforts.

animal.description: Maggie is a 2 year old  who loves to run and would be a great running partner.  She runs with abandon, and will follow her pack wherever they wander. She loves people, other dogs, cats, and has been precious with her foster mom's toddler son and 92 year old mom. She is an indoor dog, coming inside with us, lazing about the living room, and sleeping at our feet when we go to bed. She's perfectly alert, will sound off a bark to warn of new noises or something approaching but she's never been aggressive in any way. She's been the most intelligent and loving companion dog. She's part Catahoula and (I believe) Beagle since she is inclined to chase squirrels and loves a good tree. She was treated for heartworm when young and has had flea/tick prophylaxis every month in our home. She sailed through obedience training, enjoys dog parks, has been a great dog on road trips, and is both house trained and crate trained. She had her right eye removed because of glaucoma and receives drops in the left eye twice daily. She's not a chewer but will occasionally tear up a water bottle or something plastic laying about. She'll make a great dog for literally anyone and everyone that meets her adores her.  Adoption fee is $175 it includes spay/neuter, age appropriate vaccinations, rabies license, microchip, dewormer, heart worm preventative for the month, vet exam. Please go like our Facebook page at http://www.facebook.com/barkandroll . Follow us on instagram/twitter @barkandrollrc to see more pictures of me as well as other dogs in our rescue. You can access an adoption application on our website http://www.barkandrollrescuecompanions.com It usually take 1-2 days to complete the application process.

animal.description:
All dogs adopted through Troy Animal Rescue Project will be up to date on vaccinations, spayed/neutered (age appropriate), and heartworm negative before adoption. All dogs are given monthly flea/tick preventative, monthly heartworm preventative, and are dewormed regularly. Dogs adopted through Troy Animal Rescue Project are microchipped. Adoption fee is $50. Home visit and vet reference required. Applications can be put in online at http://www.troyanimalrescueproject.org/adopt.php or in person at our rescue center. ***WE DO NOT DO SAME DAY ADOPTIONS***

The address for our rescue center is 34 County Road 2266, Brundidge, AL 36010. We are one turn off Hwy 167. If you use Google maps, type in Troy Animal Rescue Project and it will take you right to us. Hours of operation are from 11-3 daily. We are open Saturdays and Sundays. No appointment necessary for pets that are located at the rescue center. Appointments must be made to visit pets in foster homes. Appointments can be made by calling 334-508-2367 or emailing troyanimalrescueproject@gmail.com. Location information will be listed beside the pets name if they are at a location other than our rescue center.

Questions can be emailed to troyanimalrescueproject@gmail.com or call 334-508-2367.

animal.description:
Pluto is a sweet chihuahua mix....looks similar to Marty McFly. He is a friendly cute fella. 1-2 years old and just about 8 lbs. He would love a forever home that would help him gain some weight.

Please find our applications and valuable information under "Adopt a dog"* on our website: *www.beaglesandbuddies.com* and email your application to beaglesandbuddies@gmail.com. Let us know your preference of appointment day/time and which dogs you are interested in and we will do our best to accommodate and email you the closest appointment available. Please allow us up to a week to get back to you. Most appointments will be Friday-Sunday, 10 am - 2 pm, for an hour.

*Note bring any other dog/s and the entire family to your meet and greet at B&B.* A complimentary training manual is included with each adoption, authored by terristeuben.com. Check out her website - she is fabulous!

B&B is glad to be open during the pandemic. We know the value and comfort of a loving pet companion and are doing our best to help the dogs and folks who need them. We update our website daily and are always rescuing, vetting, rehabilitating, socializing.

* We are accepting applications for volunteers to spend time with our dogs, hang out, sing/read to the shy ones, walk/toss ball with those who go to the playgrounds; cleaning, office work, gardening, and building/repair projects! *
Are you my furrever family?

For further info on the adoption process, please visit our home page and check out the "Adopt a Dog" section, which has thorough instructions. All our dogs are spayed/neutered, microchipped, and

fully vaccinated before adoption; they have been wormed, bathed, socialized, walked daily and much loved; each adoptee leaves with a leash, collar, and all medical records.

Our prices are higher than the shelters' because we nurse the dogs through their illnesses and get them needed surgeries and dentals. We also spend time socializing. Furthermore, unlike shelters, rescues do not get financial aid from the government and must rely on donations, grants, and adoption fees. Our fees for adults start at $150 and go up to $750. The higher end is for our most in demand dogs, such as young beagles and other purebred dogs. The lower end is for dogs who have been here a while. For puppies, we may go beyond this and charge $1000. The good news is that, because rescues fall under the "charity" category, the fees for our dogs are officially donations and are therefore tax deductible. You can think of it as donating to a worthy cause and getting a dog in return!

Sponsor Me

Beagles & Buddies must find ways to raise money so we can continue saving dogs. Your tax-deductible donation keeps our rescue kennel operating!

Hours

Friday: 10 am to 3 pm

Saturday: 10 am to 3 pm

Sunday: 10 am to 3 pm

Monday: CLOSED

Tuesday: CLOSED

Wednesday: CLOSED

Thursday: CLOSED



Weekday appointments may be available. We are a small staff and do our best to accommodate your needs. **Note that during COVID, we are not holding open houses on any day. Please email us for an appointment and include your application (found on our website, beaglesandbuddies.com, under "Forms"). Most appointments will be Friday through Sunday, though other days may also be available. We usually schedule one appointment per hour. Allow 1-2 hours for your appointment. Please look at our website and make a list of one or more dogs that you would like to see.

Contacting Us

If you have a question about adopting, giving up a dog, boarding, or volunteering, please visit the appropriate tabs on our
home page.

For more specific questions, call 626-444-9664 (please leave a voicemail if no answer) or email at beaglesandbuddies@gmail.com. Note that
Emailing
is always preferred!

Thanks!

Please note: If you are viewing this profile anywhere other than Beagles & Buddies own website, you are not receiving full info. Visit info on pet here.

animal.description:
IF INTERESTED, PLEASE SUBMIT AN APPLICATION ON OUR WEBSITE:
https://www.wonderdogrescue.org/adoption-application


NOTE: They are a bonded pair and must be adopted together. 

They are both the sweetest and really attached to each other and they need lots of time and attention from humans. They love long walks and long naps especially if you take a nap with them. They will wait for each other when walking and look for each other if they are in different rooms. Whishbone can be a little bit nervous and protective of Bailey but just needs a little bit of reassurance and attention and it will be fine. Bailey needs the scratches and will look for your attention and Wishbone will follow her on that. 

They are nice to other dogs and new people but seem not to like cats. They are well leash and potty trained and prefer sleeping on the bed with us but also take naps on their own bed.

animal.description:
One of our longest residents here at the shelter is Blaze. Blaze is often overlooked by potential adopters, but we want to change that! Our behavior coordinator Jeannie has been working closely with Blaze for months, and here are some reasons why he is her favorite dog at the shelter:



"Blaze is a beautiful hound dog with droopy ears! He is respectful and loyal to the humans he bonds with. If you take the time to get to know him, he will be your best friend. He walks great on a leash, learns commands quickly, and is so easy to train!



In his new home, Blaze would do his very best outdoors with lots of space to roam, and in the right environment, he would be the perfect working dog. He also LOVES to go for car rides. Blaze is a great dog, and he deserves a chance at the best life!"

---

Blaze is a 5 year old neutered male Bloodhound Mix. He weighs about 102 lbs and is HEARTWORM NEGATIVE. His adoption fee is $0.To learn more about how our variable adoption fees are saving more lives than ever before, please visit: http://bit.do/SPAS_Adopt

---

*Regular adoption policies and procedures apply

animal.description:
Jack is a playful 5-year old Boxer/BullMastiff mix. This handsome boy definitely has a way about him, and in the short time he has been with us, he has charmed his way into the hearts of our volunteers.

Jack loves to run and chase his toys in our dog park but his yellow ball is by far his favourite. It's very cute how much he loves his yellow ball! Always enthusiastic for an outing, Jack looks forward to his daily walks and he is very good on leash. He listens well and knows how to heel, sit, lie down and he will even roll over when asked. When he is relaxed and feels secure, Jack is a happy, fun and playful dog. He also loves car rides.

Jack is, however, fearful and uncertain when meeting new people, especially men. At the shelter, when in his kennel or outdoor pen, his tendency is to bark when approached by someone he does not know, but if you ignore him, and let him come to you, he settles down. It is important that visitors understand and respect this. Once he gets to know you and feels at ease, he is an affectionate, lovable, friendly and loyal dog who likes to be with people. Because of his fearfulness, Jack must be placed into a home with a dog savvy adopter who understands his needs and will help him build his confidence in a secure and stable environment. Jack should not live in a home with children and he should be the only animal in the household. He isn’t great with other dogs, especially dominant males but he doesn’t seek out trouble and he can be walked with other dogs as long as the person at the other end of the leash is attentive and in control.

Because of his looks, breed specific legislation (BSL) may apply so before inquiring, please be sure that Jack is welcome in your town, city or municipality.

animal.description:
Tess is a sweet loving girl that loves people and children!! Unfortunately she may be aggressive to certain dogs if she feels threatened. If exposed to other dogs she should be muzzled.  She loves being brushed, petted, going on car rides and simply soaking in the sun when it is nice outside. If we show her kittens she is very gentle but we aren't sure if she could be trusted with older cats, she is selective on the cats and dogs that she likes and dislikes so caution should be taken and she may do better as a only pet. Sweet Tess has been at the shelter since July 2020 and has been patiently waiting for her perfect family to find her, could you be the one?

Tess est une fille douce et aimante qui aime les gens et les enfants !! Malheureusement, elle peut être très agressive envers certains chiens si elle se sent menacée. Si elle est exposée à d'autres chiens, elle doit être muselée. Elle adore se faire brosser, caresser, faire des promenades en voiture et simplement se baigner au soleil quand il fait beau dehors. Si nous lui montrons des chatons elle est très douce mais nous ne savons pas si on peut lui faire confiance avec des chats plus âgés. Elle est très sélective sur les chats et les chiens qu'elle aime et n'aime pas, alors il faut être prudent. Elle pourrait faire mieux en tant que seule animal de compagnie. Layla's fosterer writes...
I am a sweetheart with all humans–I just love to be loved and to give love to everyone! (Well, maybe not the letter carrier.)

However, I get on high alert when I see another dog, so you will need to avoid encounters when we are out walking. Someone trained me well, and I have perfect manners. My foster parents got me when I needed surgery for two fractures in a front leg, but that is all healed now–thanks, SPCA!– and I enjoy running around in the yard playing keep-away, and taking several long walks each day. Frequent brushing keeps my coat looking good and manageable.

If you are seeking a close companion who will be your best friend and walking partner, and we can avoid other animals, I’m your gal.

Please consult our ADOPTION FAQ (http://www.pgspca.org/adopt/frequently-asked-questions/)  before contacting us.  If you are viewing this listing on a site that is not Petfinder or Adoptapet, please check our main site: 
http://www.pgspca.org/adopt/adoptable-animals-2
for the most up-to-date information on this pet.

If you are interested in Layla, consider letting us know by filling out a (no-obligation) adoption application (http://www.pgspca.org/adopt/online-adoption-application/) and we will arrange a meeting.
To see if Layla will be attending the next adoption show, check here: http://www.pgspca.org/adopt/adoption-show-attendees/.

NOTE: We are an all-volunteer group and do not operate a shelter. All of our animals are in foster homes. Due to our requirement for a home visit, we generally only place animals within an hour's drive of Washington, DC. Questions can be directed to pgspca.adopt@gmail.com.

animal.description:
Neptune is a sweet 50 lb. 1-year-old Lab-Husky mix with gorgeous blue eyes who is looking for his forever home. He gets along with and loves to play with all dogs but may chase your cat for fun.  If your cat defends itself, Neptune is a big sissy and he'll likely turn and run. 

Neptune is good on a leash, and house and crate trained.  He is a medium active boy who would love to be a part of your walking or hiking routine. He would be fine with kids over 12 due to his size.  If you would like to learn more about Neptune, please complete an application and then reach out to Roxy@bigfluffydogs.com.

If you are interested in adopting this dog, please apply online, at https://bigfluffydogs.com/adopt/adoption-application/. 

Our main website, www.bigfluffydogs.com has more information about us and the rescue process. 

NOTE TO EMAILERS FROM PETFINDER: WE DO NOT RESPOND TO EMAIL INQUIRIES WITHOUT AN APPLICATION. WE REGRET WE CANNOT RESPOND TO EVERY EMAIL, BUT UNLESS YOU FILL OUT AN APPLICATION, WE DO NOT KNOW YOU EXIST. 

All known information about an individual dog is provided in its listing. We do our best to provide accurate information, but adopters should understand that each home is different and the dog may behave differently in a new home. Dogs are creatures of their environment and you help make the dog what it will be. Homes considering adopting a puppy must be prepared for 1.) Flexible schedules for potty training. Puppies can only hold it for one hour per month of age (i.e. a 4-month-old puppy can only go 4 hours without a potty break). 2.) Crate training until the puppy is at least one year old to prevent chewing on inappropriate things when you can't supervise. 3.) Socialization.  The more positive and varying experiences as a puppy the better, both in and out of your home. 4.) Puppy behavior and life stages are equivalent to a human toddler. It takes at least a full year to have a calmer, well-adjusted dog. Patience is required and when your dog's behavior is a positive experience for you and those around you, your patience will be rewarded ten-fold, for years to come.  Please do not consider adopting a puppy if you have not thoroughly thought through the pros and cons of having one. So many people end up returning them after 3-5 months because they didn't realize the amount of work involved in raising a puppy.  Patience, appropriate toys, socialization, and obedience training are all musts. All are time-consuming and can be expensive. All dogs require supervision with children and obedience training. Adopters that want to have good dogs must be prepared to put the time and effort into training a dog. Any dog requires work and effort, but a well trained, well-socialized dog is more than worth the effort to get them there.

animal.description:
THIS SITUATION IS URGENT

Maya previously Landry

Located in Eastern NE
1 year old
American Bulldog/ Mastiff/Labrador/Boxer mix is our best guess
Previously ok with some dogs and not with others, currently in a single dog home
Cats unknown, chases but adopter believes it's playful 
Good with kids but can be hyper, nippy and strong so keep that in mind
House trained 
Perfectly crate trained and knows some commands
Stays off furniture 
Only chews on toys 
Fully vetted
Very strong
Must have a 6' privacy fence 
65lbs approximately 

Maya, previously Landry, is one of Tatums puppies. She originally went to a foster to adopt home but that just didn't work out, not due to her, and she went to a long term foster. That foster home adored her, they had a cat that she tried to play with but the cat wasn't a fan. They ended up having to move to another state however they had a coworker who was interested in adopting. They met Maya and adopted her at the end of the Summer and we heard nothing else. We were contacted at the end of November by the husband stating that they had decided that due to some behavioral issues Maya wasn't a good fit and they needed to "move on." This was obviously shocking and heartbreaking to us. We asked for details as to the behavioral issues and contacted the trainer who they consulted once. 

These are the 3 main concerns:
She "zones in" on a person and jumps at them sometimes nipping. The older kids and adults are fine but with the younger kids this was an issue.
She chases cats
Leash reactive to other animals 

This girl deserves a FURever home familiar with strong dog breeds. We are willing to pay for a couple secessions with a trainer if adopted/fostered in Eastern NE. 

The adopter is threatening to give her away against our contract and against our approval. Due to this and just because we want her in a home that actually wants her there, we need her moved ASAP. This situation is URGENT.

Original Post

Landry was being adopted by her foster family and unfortunately they have now changed their mind.
The problem is we have turned down several adoption applications for her believing she was being adopted by her fosters. Now she's available again as she isn't getting along with their chihuahua. She is also a protective dog, as mastiffs are, and needs a mastiff experienced owner. We believe that some of the issues are environmental as this is the 2nd dog that had had the same issues with this family. Her foster family also just had another baby and it's just a lot for Landry. She is a sweet and happy go lucky girl who loves her people and deserves an amazing FURever family! 

If interested please contact us!

 $200.00 Adoption Fee 
(The $200.00 is considered a nonrefundable donation and being we are a 501c3 organization it is tax deductible. The fee itself is not negotiable, our vets don't negotiate and thus neither do we).

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.
Name: Fuego
DOB: 4/20/2018
Weight: 10 lbs
Adoption Fee: 400.00

Fuego is looking for a very experienced chihuahua owner. Don't be fooled by his gorgeous appearance, he has "issues" and cannot go to a home with children. He is a bite case surrender from Texas. whoever adopts him, will have to sign a form saying they understand this. He needs continuing training to overcome his "triggers". He LOVES his daily training sessions with me involving his harness. Possible abuse may have led to some things becoming uncomfortable for him and he responds with the "fight" response, in an instant. For Fuego to be successful in his new home, he should have a fenced in yard. One cannot easily put a harness on him; so no walks, same goes for a collar and belly band. I am able to put a muzzle on him, as this is not one of his triggers, but he shouldn't wear it for long periods of time. He is so good at going potty outside, but tends to mark a little indoors, on new items, as there is another boy here that likes to mark. It's a competition apparently. For vet visits and nail trims, we have discovered Gabapentin is a MUST. There is no other way. Works great. On to the good stuff... Fuego LOVES my youngest chihuahua, Sunnie. They play for hours and hours and he is so good with her. He is also really good with my other chihuahuas, but tends be very aggressive if his food/treat is monopolized. I can easily give him treats directly to his mouth. He tends to guard bones that are lying around, though. He loves his kennel, and sleeps in it at night and during the day. Fuego is incredibly loving. He jumps and "smiles" when he wants attention and when I come home from work. He will jump up on my lap and demand pets and he loves to be brushed and pet, even his belly! He scoots closer and closer on his butt to get pets. It's so stinking cute. Since I learned his triggers, we have lived happily ever after. It is easy to avoid what makes him tick, he just needs that chance.

In the meantime, if you have questions or are interested in me, please fill out an adoption application at www.ruffstartrescue.org.

An adoption application is the best way to show your interest in an animal.

Please check out our website, www.ruffstartrescue.org for more details and additional pictures on any of our animals!

All Ruff Start dogs and cats are spayed/neutered, up to date on age-appropriate vaccines, microchipped, dewormed, and on monthly flea/tick and heartworm prevention (dogs) as well as heartworm tested (dogs).

Ruff Start Rescue is a foster-based rescue. Animals are located in homes throughout Minnesota. We do not have a facility where animals are kept.

animal.description:
Please note: Due to high volume email inquires cannot not be returned. Please go to our website, (socorescue.com) complete an online application and indicate which animal(s) you are interested in. Once approved, you will be contacted to schedule an adoption appointment. Thank you for your patience.

Annabelle was nursing a litter of pups when she found as a stray within our area. We're not sure if she was abandoned after her litter was born or became pregnant while homeless, only that she was in dire need of being rescued. All of her pups have gone on to find their new homes, but Annabelle had to remain with us while we got her back to good health as she was extremely malnourished and heartworm positive when she arrived.

Annabelle is very people friendly but tends to be a little reserved when first meeting new people. She will bark at people she isn't familiar with, making her a great option for someone looking for a family companion that will also ward off strangers. Give Annabelle a couple of days to get acquainted with you and she'll be your best friend and more than happy to receive belly rubs and being playful with you. We think that Annabelle will do best in a low commotion type of home and one without young children. Annabelle has preferred being without the company of other dogs and we're not sure if that will change once in a new home.

In addition to being treated for her heartworms, Annabelle has also been fully vetted and kept on her monthly flea/tick and heartworm preventatives. A microchip will accompany her adoption. She has displayed signed of having once been housetrained but may require a refresher course once in a home.

To apply for the adoption of this wonderful girl, please submit an application at socorescue.com

animal.description:
Hi my name is Deano. I'm a 2-3yr old terrier/shih tzu mix and weigh around 15-18lbs.  I was rescued from a shelter in the Houston area by Camo Rescue. My home was "on the streets" before Camo Rescue saved me!!! I'm vaccinated, neutered, and microchipped. I am currently going through heartworm treatment. As I "wormed" (yes that's a thing) into my foster Mom's heart, she has taken very good care of me! I am not sure about the places she takes me, but do love to go in the car. Back seat please! My foster Mom has this weird look on her face because I don't bark! I do like to know where she is most of the time but am very good on a leash (as long as there are no big dogs), I just want to run when I see them. I'm crate and potty trained. My foster mom thinks I will be great in almost any home and with older children. I"m sure chill so it may take me a bit to warm up in a new environment only due to my yucky past. I hope I have pulled at your heart strings, it would be nice to find my forever home. 

ALL adoptions require a completed application, vet check, home check and final contract.  The application to adopt can be found at www.camorescue.com.

Adoption fees are variable. Up to date vaccines, microchip, spay/neuter are included in the fee.

Once your application has been approved, we will put you in touch with the foster to set up a  meet and greet. We are a foster based RESCUE, not a shelter. All of our dogs are in individual foster homes. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. We select the best applicant for each dog, based on the dog's needs. 
For the safety of our small breed dogs and based on our past experiences, we will not place our dogs in homes with large breed dogs.    

CAMO rescue is a 501c3 whose primary focus is rescuing small dogs from the euthanasia list from high kill TX shelters.   
EIN # is 46-5486022
We rescue 800+ animals a year.

Follow us on Facebook at www.facebook.com/camorescue

Our donation link is http://www.paypalme/camorescue 

We are strictly volunteer based, no salaries are paid and 100% of donations go towards rescuing dogs.

I'm also really smart and am prepared with the knowledge of some basic commands. While I'm doing well at OFSDS, I wish more than anything to have a home of my own! Are you or is someone you know looking for a guy like me? I'm ready!"

animal.description:
Our precious girl Kiwi is 45 lbs of cuddle bug! We aren’t quite sure of her breed, she’s definitely a mutt, we know she is for sure 100% adorable!! We think she has Boxer, some Shar-Pei, and possibly some Vizsla. She is around 2 years old and is as sweet as can be. 

Kiwi will love her person so much and she loves to give kisses on the hand, but is a little shy at first. She can be wary of men and would do better in a home with women or with a couple that is willing to work with her. Once she warms up to you, she’s your best friend, and your lap dog, especially if you give her all the petting she wants. 

She is friendly with other dogs while on walks but is not well socialized and needs to get to know any canine companions. Kiwi has a bit of a prey instinct and would probably not do well with cats. 

Kiwi is an active dog that loves to go for walks/runs and hikes and loves doing zoomies. She walks well on a leash, enjoys a nice patio, and likes to hang in the backyard with you. Although she is active she will settle in nicely and nap or cuddle.

She does well with older kids, while she is working on learning not to jump up for attention. Smaller children will probably get knocked down with her energetic behavior. 

This smart girl is house broken and crate trained. She also knows basic commands like, “sit”, “stay”, “kennel”, “place”, and “off”. 

If you’re looking for a sweet, smart, and loyal companion, Kiwi is your girl.

animal.description:
CHARLIE 
This sweet boy, only 2 years old and 55 lbs was rescued from a bad situation by a good samaritan who can foster him only until January. Charlie was living in a back yard with very occasional food and water until he was rescued.

This rough start has not gotten Charlie down.
He is a happy-go-lucky, friendly and sweet guy despite his rough start. He get's along with everyone he meets. 
He is a playful and silly pup with lot's of personality and fun. He brings laughter to his foster family's home and is an excellent house guest.

Charlie has been living in his foster home and learning how to be a house dog. He is receiving some training  from our AFLAR trainer to help him learn good canine manners. He is crate trained. He is learning good leash manners and would love two walks a day and a back yard to play with his family in.
Charley would also do well as an only dog so he get's all the love and attention he has been missing.

Charlie's ideal home would be an active home where his family has time to continue his training and give him the love, leadership and stability that he needs to thrive.
He would do fine with older children and we don't know about cats.

If you're interested in meeting Charley, please contact.
Info@AllForLoveAnimalRescue.org
fill out an application. www.allforloveanimalrescue.org
(805) 445-3535

animal.description:
Koda is a lovely affectionate puppy that loves to play and run like the wind. He is nearly 9 months old and an energetic boy who seems to be good with dogs after slow introductions and is indifferent to dog savvy cats. He has settled in well, but is nervous about meeting people and other dogs at first. But give him a little time and he will warm up and play. HIs favourite game is running around with a ball in his mouth, can't really call it fetch because he doesn't like to bring it back!. But he is also happy to settle down with his foster brother to chew - either a toy or the foster brother.
We are working on manners, he knows how to Come, and Sit and is pretty good about "No", also he is also good on a leash with a harness and likes car rides. He is a lightweight Dane ...possible mix because he was found as a pup behind a store. He has no idea how big he is, so he tends to be all over the place, when he isn't being a velcro Dane with a big lean and the back up sit.
He is a busy boy, seldom still for long and really beautiful to watch running such a graceful boy.

https://greatdanefriends.com/koda

Please contact Great Dane Friends (info@greatdanefriends.com) for more information about this pet.

*****Great Dane Friends of Ruff Love covers NC and surrounding states for adoptions. We require a fenced yard (exceptions made on a case by case basis - NO exceptions for puppies or deaf/vision impaired dogs - no invisible fencing), that stairs in the home be covered with some sort of slip resistant material to prevent injury, that all other animals in the home be up to date on vaccinations as well as spayed/neutered and that all dogs live inside as a part of the family. Our approval process consists of an application, vet and reference checks, phone interview and house check. Please email us for an application or if you have any questions.*****

animal.description:
Hi! My name is Delta...and I need a job. All the time. My previous family got me, thinking happy and pretty evens out very active and smarter than most people. That is not the case so to the shelter I went. It is true, I am beautiful. I am also going to be huge, powerful and solid. It is also true that I am happy and sweet. I love everyone. Dogs, people, everyone. But I am VERY true to my breed and NEED an outlet for my energy and brains. If you cannot meet those needs, I am not the dog or breed for you. I pick up on things very quickly but need a family that understands my breed and my need to have a job and ensure I understand I am not the boss. I am going to make the right family an AWESOME family member and partner in crime.

I AM NOW READY TO GO HOME!! If you are approved to be my new family, a hold fee of $100 is required and will be applied to the full adoption fee of $350 when MVPC comes to visit your house with me! 

ADOPTION FEE: $350 (All MVPC dogs are heartworm-tested, completely vetted, spayed/neutered, microchipped, crate-trained and house-trained)
ADOPTER: MUST have WORKING DOG experience. A MALE dog currently in the home for socialization is preferred.
BIRTHDAY: Estimated 5-6 months
FENCE: Required (an electric fence is not an acceptable form of containment)
DOGS: Yes
CATS: Yes
CHILDREN: Yes, over 5 please

INQUIRIES: ALL inquiries begin with a submitted adoption application, which is found on our website, www.miamivalleypitcrew.com. We do not adopt to individuals under the age of 25. We prefer male/female pairings unless both already reside in the home. 

DO NOT: USE THE PETFINDER CONTACT/ADOPT BUTTONS--we are unable to monitor those and you will not receive a response. 

PLEASE NOTE: We are volunteer based and a home visit is required; we have a two-hour adoption radius from Kettering, OH for our adult dogs and 75 miles for our puppies. Exceptions for our ADULT dogs only, though rare, may be made on a case-by-case basis but we must be able to do a home visit. Thank you for 

Professional holiday and Valentine’s Day pictures courtesy of the talented Gwen Estep Photography, LLC https://www.facebook.com/GwenEstepPhotography/

She is a happy girl, affectionate with a constantly wagging tail. If you're looking for an addition to your family, Loretta is available for adoption. 

Loretta is a gentle 9 year old female lab mix.  She is very well behaved, has a calm disposition and is housebroken. She is happiest when she can sit next to you and get head and belly rubs.  She is a good walker and still has a playful side.  She knows how to sit and comes when called.  She gets along fine with cats but would be best with large dogs or as an only dog (not recommended with very small dogs).  She is being treated for heartworms but the vet said her heart sounds very strong.  She still has a lot of love to give and would make such a loving and loyal addition to any family.

animal.description: Hi!  My name is Jack!  I need a home because my person passed away. I'm playful & I love to have my belly rubbed! I love attention & affection! I'm full of energy! I'm a very smart fellow & I learn quickly! I've lived all my life with 3 other male beagles (also available for adoption) outside as a hunting dog.  But I'm ready to come in & be part of a family! I'm very affectionate & love people! Because I haven't been around young children, I will be placed in a home with older children (8-12 years) or no children. I need a home where I will have a securely fenced yard. I have been known to dig under a fence, so it needs to be secure. I will run off looking for bunnies to chase if I get loose.  I've been learning to walk on a leash since I came to Nittany Beagle Rescue (have a martingale collar & that helps a lot!).  Because I never went anywhere, I'm pretty timid in new situations. Because I've lived all my life outside, I will need work on housetraining & house manners. But I lived in a hutch in my old home, & so I have the idea about going outside vs. inside - so that is a very big start! Nittany Beagle Rescue can provide advice on housetraining & house manners - we actually find it easier to housetrain older dogs than puppies (older dogs focus better!). Jack seems to be good with other dogs. He will chase cats if they run, but we think if someone worked with him on that, he would stop. Jack is a big boy! He barks in a crate, but the more he has exposure to being crated, the better he is doing in them. He does better in metal crates. We need a foster home for Jack so he can start learning about living inside the home with the family. If you aren't ready to adopt, please think about fostering him!

animal.description:
Sweetie pie Dezzy!
Dezzy is a boxer mix, with a tender, sweet, loving personality.  She enjoys taking walks and walks nice on a leash. Dezzy can be a silly girl too, showing that she still has plenty of energy for fun, zooming around the outside runs, but she is most happy to be near someone who wants to give her affection.  Dezzy does like to take a moment or two to check out new people, but she does warm up pretty quickly especially if you have yummy treats and talk to her - she loves to be talked to and told what a good girl she is.
Dezzy is 7 years old and weighs approximately 57 pounds.  She is well mannered; knows how to sit and shake hands when asked (probably lay down too) and is potty trained.
Dezzy may do better in a home where she is the only pet, but she does have a calm, respectful male dog friend she walks with at the shelter. She is such a sweet dog she will be sure to bring her forever home plenty of love and fun. Due to her reserved nature we recommend any children in the home are older teenagers.

If you would like to meet Dezzy, please fill out a no obligation adoption application at:  https://wishbonepetrescue.org/adopt/adoption-applications/ and an appointment will be set up for you to come in and meet sweetie pie Dezzy

animal.description:
Update 12/11/2020. Posted 12/7/2020. My name is Ajax and I am looking for a home with lots of patience. I need a family that wants to take me to see the world. I am a 8 month old Cattle Dog mix who was found running. I was such a scared puppy when I was trapped that I didn’t do well with the shelter and the shelter workers. I would get as far back in to my cage as possible and if the shelter works would reach in at me I would growl and snap at them. I was on the euthanasia list. My foster mommy saw my picture on a list and couldn’t let me die so she got me transported to PA. I am doing really good in my foster home. I am learning that people are awesome. I would do better with another friendly dog in the house as they help give me confidence and teach me the ropes. I also need a fenced in yard to keep me safe. I am crate trained and house broken. I like going for walks and car rides. Help me find that forever home.

Adoption application, home visit and adoption fee required. If you would like to apply for adoption, please complete the online application at www.furryfriendsnetwork.com. Look under ADOPT tab. Please also read our Core Values prior to applying. Contact generalinfo@furryfriendsnetwork.com for questions or if issues are encountered with the adoption application or general adoption process.

Foster Homes are desperately needed in order to help more animals like this one. Please consider opening your heart and home to a homeless animal. To find out more about becoming a Foster Parent, see our website at www.furryfriendsnetwork.com. Look under VOLUNTEER tab.

animal.description:
Hiiiii! I'm Dutchess, an 8-year-old American Bulldog and I'm a big girl (over 90 lbs!). I used to live on a property with 4 other dogs and a few people, but we were kept outside and didn't have a fence. We would occasionally wander off and cause trouble in the neighborhood, we were basically a dog pack. After a while of not receiving proper care, Dog Control got involved and the court ordered that I be taken to a safe place, which ended up being Stray Haven! The staff has learned a lot about me in the time I've been here and have determined that I need a particular type of adopter. I bond deeply with my people. As I got more and more comfortable with the staff who care for me here, I decided I didn't really want to meet new people when I'd go on meet and greets with potential adopters. I might go and accept a treat from a stranger, but I'd then sit right back next to my staff/family. I have decided the staff is my new family so why would I want to meet new people? I definitely have the ability to bond with new people however. I didn't know the staff when I came in, and look at us now! I can also feel what type of ""vibe"" a human is giving off and I'm really good at knowing if a person is a good fit for me. I am not shy, on the contrary, I'm a very confident gal and know what I want. Because I'm a bigger girl, the staff wants to make sure I go to a home with people who understand my breed and are confident dog handlers. Although I used to live with dogs, now that I'm older, I don't want to live with dogs anymore, I'm just not a fan. But that's OK, just more of me to love! I'm not sure how I would do with kids either. I did live with kids, but I wasn't in the house until they were teenagers. I would have to meet any youngsters first to see how I like them. Here at Stray Haven I approached some caged cats, and I didn't really seem to care. If you have a cat it's best to give the cat a safe space and not introduce us for a week or two at least. I am definitely a special girl and although I'm not for everyone, I would be great for someone who is a confident dog owner and loves a smart dog. I don't need much exercise at all, and since I'm in my golden years as a bigger breed, I am likely only going to get slower over time. I would love a home with structure/rules, and loving, dog savvy owners where I can be the only dog. If you think you are the one for me, let's talk! Ask the staff for some more information and how to meet with me.
Stray Haven Humane Society & SPCA
194 Shepard Rd., Waverly, NY 14892
(607) 565-2859, www.strayhavenspca.org 
Open hours (winter): Tues, Wed & Thurs Noon - 6pm; Sat 10am-4pm

animal.description:
SPECIAL NEEDS/ VISION IMPAIRED

Zeus is a house trained 85lb, 2yr old male American Bulldog. He was born blind, however is well adjusted (as all dogs born blind) and knows how to navigate with his heightened other senses and can memorize his surroundings. Zeus communicates to let you know he needs to go outside. He enjoys playing with other dogs, walks, etc. He loves to socialize with other people and animals while outside and on walks. He honestly has the most laid back and loving personality of any dog. He loves being with people, especially if he can snuggle. He also prefers to be in the company of other dogs. He needs a home where hes not left alone for long periods of time and that has another dog. Zeus also requires a fully fenced yard.

Zeus is neutered, heartworm negative and is up to date on vaccines, rabies, heartworm and flea preventative.

Applications can be filled out and submitted online using this link https://petstablished.com/adoption_form/25085/generic

animal.description:
Venom is a big boy weighing at around 80-85 lbs. Some may say he looks intimidating but he's really just a big ol teddy bear. He's great with kids and people of all sizes. Great with other dogs too but does sometimes try to "hump" them. We don't think he will do well with cats but he's never been properly tested. He prefers to be with his human as much as possible but also does ok in a crate for a reasonable amount of time. 

Back story: He was pulled from a local shelter's euthanasia list after being picked up as a stray. He had a limp but we assumed it was nothing major since he was still using his leg. We later found out he needed a total hip replacement. They thought he may have been hit by a car at some point. Well, he got the surgery and it was a long road to recovery but he is 100% now and ready to find his perfect forever.

animal.description: Please welcome the star of the CBS hit special: Everybody Loves Ramona! Ramona, is the star of the couch potato series, and she is looking for her co-star, in what critics are calling a box office special. Ramona has an idea of what her set and crew members look like, and has provided a list: *A low-traffic home, either an apartment or a house with a yard, as long as there is room on the couch for her queen-sized frame. *A family, with mostly adults because she likes her crew to understand that she likes adults who respect her space. *Humans who will kindly give and receive an endless amount of hugs and kisses, with her record-winning large tongue. Ramona knows what she wants, and if you're willing to provide that for her, she will multiply the love and affection in return, at no cost. animal.description:
MEET LAYLA 6!!

From Layla's foster: Layla came to our home undernourished and hand shy. She initially got along with our other dogs but as she gained strength she became aggressive toward our female and the two engage in fights every time they are together. ,Layla is crate trained and we do have a crate for her to take with to her forever home. ,She knows, sit, stay, and wait (for food). Because she was underfed she was very food aggressive, but we have worked with her and she is much improved. She also far less hand shy and is no longer fearful of quick body movements. We have a cat that she wants to play with but he is not good with dogs at all so we do not know how she would do with a playful cat. Layla has not been dog park tested. Layla is very good on car rides and good on walks. She does become excited around other animals and will chase but stops when verbally corrected. Layla is pretty shy when meeting new people but warms up to them with encouragement. She loves belly rubs and snuggles. Layla is on all natural dog food and some foods upset her digestion. (This is why she is listed as special needs). Layla's ideal forever home would be one where she is the only pet and can go everywhere with her human.

If you are interested in meeting this dog, please visit our website for our online application www.underdogaz.com

PLEASE NOTE: This dog is courtesy posted for another individual or Rescue. Different policies and fees may apply.

animal.description:
Wesley is a shy kinda fella - he likes people, but it takes him a bit to get over his shyness. He was abandoned by his owner and this shook his confidence. Wesley is not a cuddle bug kinda guy, he is more of a quiet guy who is happy to keep you company but without all the touchy feely stuff. Just like people, some enjoy being the life of the party, others prefer calmness and quiet. That is our Wesley. For that reason, we recommend an adult only home for this guy.

Don't let Wesley's XL size fool you. Wesley still scares easily - loud noises, strangers coming up quickly behind him..he will startle and needs reassurance. Wesley loves to get out and enjoy walks in the park and getting exercise. He just needs love, reassurance and patience as he works on his confidence.

He is currently enrolled in training and is doing great. He is totally unfazed by the other dogs in his class and happily follows the commands his handler gives him.

Please go to our website and complete an adoption application at:

/https://www.gsroc.org/application/

An adoption counselor will contact you to go over your application and assist you in determining which dog may be best for your particular situation.

animal.description:
Molly is a young Black Labrador mix who is about 1 year old and came to us as a stray from the pound. Therefore we have no previous information on her history. 
Molly is in a foster home with other dogs and cats. She has not been around kids.
Molly would not do well with toddlers or small children and with her energy level would knock them over.
Molly has lots of energy and would not do well in an apartment setting but needs an active family with a fenced yard and room to run off energy. 
Molly's house training is a work in progress - lots of accidents in the home and working on crate training. 
***Molly was having lots of potty accidents. 
Tested urine and she has urinary tract infection and crystals in the urine.  Molly will need to be on prescription food during her lifetime to prevent uti and crystals. Cost of prescription food for a #25 pound bag is about $85 per month.****
Molly is smart and so willing to please her family. 
All medical work is completed prior to adoption including spay shots worming flea treatment rabies shot micro chip snd vet exam. 
The adoption fee is $150 + tax with an approved application.  The application is on the website www.prairiepawsrescue.com and go to the adopt link to download the jotform application fill it out and submit 
Prairie Paws Rescue does not adopt on a first come basis but who will provide the best home suited to the pets needs.

Meet this sweet boy named Christian! Christian is a very nice, 3 year old boy looking for a new home to call his own! He was found as a lost boy on 11/30. Christian has a super cute and curious personality. So far, Christian has been quiet in his run, but he gets very curious about the squeaky toys. With so much adventuring, Christian will need some time to cuddle and get some much needed TLC from his new family. Meet this 57 pound sweetheart in run 853. His ID number is 626259. Christian is up-to-date on vaccines, now neutered, and will be microchipped, and heart worm tested upon adoption. He can't wait to love his new family. 

Please note, all of the pet listings on Friends of Shelter Animals for Cobb are done by volunteers, not shelter staff. If this pet came in as lost (not an owner surrender), we don't know how they might be with children, other pets, or if house trained. You can bring your pet to the shelter for a meet & greet with your potential new best friend. When calling the shelter about a cat or dog, please use THE ID NUMBER, names are oftentimes made up by volunteers. 

This pet and many others are available for adoption from the Cobb County Animal Shelter 1060 Al Bishop Dr. Marietta, GA 30008, call (770) 499-4136 for more information. Shelter hours are: Tues. - Sun. 10:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. by appointment only until further notice, CLOSED Mondays & Holidays.

animal.description:
Meet Henry~

My name is Henry and I am a 1 year old Boston Terrier/ Chi mix from South Carolina.  I weigh roughly 23 lbs.

Henry is a cute little guy for sure! He does have some of the little dog mentality though we have recently found out. He will need a home where he will not be allowed to run the show. Henry needs a confident handler who will teach him what behaviors are acceptable and not acceptable. This guy can definitely be a brat sometimes!
With proper training and guidance, this little guy will make a fantastic little bud!

 With my adorable looks, and unbridled loyalty, I will always be there for you through thick and thin. I will never judge you, or turn my back on you. Every single day, you will look at me and you will know that you are loved unconditionally. I will never betray you or hurt you, and I will grow old by your side.

******IMPORTANT - PLEASE READ ALL THE GREAT INFO BELOW******

***Please don't apply unless you are very serious about adopting, and are ready to move forward with the adoption process. We are super busy and make a great effort to respond back to EVERYONE ASAP! WHEN WE TAKE THE TIME TO PROCESS AN APPLICATION AND RESPOND BACK TO THE APPLICANT JUST TO BE EITHER IGNORED OR BE TOLD THEY CANNOT COME FOR SEVERAL DAYS, MORE TIME IS WASTED~PLEASE HAVE MORE RESPECT THAN THAT!

PLEASE read our website's ADOPTION PROCESS PAGE prior to submitting an adoption application. www.apupspizzazzrescue.com/adoption-process 
ADOPTION APPLICATION: www.apupspizzazzrescue.com/adoption-application 

ABOUT OUR RESCUE DOGS: 
 All of our dogs are located in Connecticut, are spayed or neutered, up to date on vaccines, microchipped, have been given deworming medications, and have had CT State health checks, & go home with a leash, collar, & packet of medical paperwork. 

BREED IDENTIFICATION:
Please understand that many rescue dogs are mixes of multiple breeds. Petfinder allows us to choose up to two breeds per dog. While the shelters and our rescue do our best in accurately identifying breeds, breed identification is not guaranteed. If there is a certain breed that you do not want, it is very important that you share this with our rescue when applying. When adopting a puppy, breed uncertainty plays a big part in the size/look of the dog as an adult. Please know that any puppy can be a wonderful dog, regardless of preconceived notions of certain breeds, but it is very important that the adopter has the dedication and patience to raise the puppy with boundaries, consistency, structure, & love. The more effort you give towards training & time you allow for exercise, your puppy will grow to be a HUGE source of UNCONDITIONAL LOVE, TOTAL LOYALTY, HAPPINESS, COMFORT & COMPANIONSHIP!

ABOUT OUR RESCUE:
We are a small rescue run by volunteers & focused on finding the right match for both our dogs & for you. If you are interested in adopting through our rescue, you first will need to complete an adoption application & be approved as a potential adopter before meeting any of our pups. No need to be intimidated by our application as it allows us to get to know you & your lifestyle. Of course, the more you can share the better! Please also note, while a fenced yard is fantastic, it is not required by our rescue, however, it may be required for a certain dog occasionally.  Once adoption applicants are approved to become potential adopters, we offer private appointments where you can meet one or several dogs at the discretion of the rescue. We offer a unique & pleasant experience focused on finding the perfect match. It is extremely important to us that everyone is treated with respect & that NO ONE IS LEFT HANGING. WE WILL GET BACK TO YOU WITHIN 2 TO 3 DAYS of application submission. If there is a dog you are eager to meet, please  TEXT US DIRECTLY at 203-241-2351 so that we can check the status of your application and move it forward immediately. We look forward to hearing from you and helping you find your new best friend.

*All adult dogs can be cat tested by request.

HOME/RENTER INSURANCE:
SOME PROVIDERS HAVE VERY STRICT POLICIES REGARDING WHICH TYPE OF DOG BREEDS ARE ALLOWED UNDER THEIR COVERAGE. STATE FARM WAS SUGGESTED TO US AS THEY DO NOT PUNISH, DROP, NOR REFUSE YOU DUE TO DOG BREED SHOULD YOU RUN INTO ISSUES WITH YOUR CURRENT PROVIDER.

animal.description:
CHARMAINE (female)
Breed: Laborador
Age: approx. 2 years
Weight: approx. 40 - 45 lbs.
Adopter Experiece: Intermediate - Advanced.
Charmaine is a typical playful, curious lab but not a dog for a novice handler. She has been socialized with dogs of all sizes and has done well but tends to be bit shy/timid of new humans. Charmaine would be fine children over 12 years but a home with young children is not ideal. Previous shy dog experience preferred.
ADOPTION REQUIREMENTS & PROCEDURES

Mutt Match L.A. does not adopt out of state nor do we adopt on a first come first serve basis but rather to the home that is best suited for each particular dog and breed. An application, home check, contract and adoption fee are required for all adoptions. All dogs will be, or required to be, spayed/neutered, current on vaccinations and microchipped before adoption. Most of our dogs are from local LA area shelters, we generally have no prior history for them.

Adoption fees vary between $350 - $450 for puppies 8 weeks - 8 years, $300 for dogs 8 years and over. Adoption fee covers spay/neuter, vaccinations, microchip a wellness check, any additional medical expenses necessary and of course the all the love and daily care we take with each dog before they are adopted.

We believe a well behaved dog is a happy dog and companion. Therefore, we require at least one session with one of our recommended behaviorists for a reduced fee which is not included in the adoption fee.

For additional information or questions, please email us at info@muttmatchla.org. To submit an application, please visit us at www.muttmatchla.org. Mutt Match L.A. is an all volunteer rescue, please allow at least 48 hours for a returned response of all inquires. No additional photos are available, photos are updated as received.

Thank you! We look forward to hearing from you soon.

Max
1.5 yo male
Brindle
70 pounds
Slow Intros to Dogs
Older Teen Friendly
No Cats
Crate & Leash Trained
NEEDS ROUTINE & STRUCTURE
Fostered in Sandy, Oregon

Hi my name is Max! I guess you could say I am a "to the Max" kind of fur kid. As
in, I am a bit scared of little people and a chaotic roomful of people and dogs
causes me stress and anxiety.
I thrive on routine and structure. I have been getting lots of good training time in
to give me some awesome coping skills, so I would love a family that would
continue with my training. I'm looking for a loving human who will provide me the
security and safety I need to relax as my best doggie self. You know the kind,
snack a little, play, watch movies, take some easy walks, snuggle, get belly rubs,
you know dog stuff. I have not had much just plain dog living in my life and I find
myself getting really excited about the idea. I love a big backyard so I can do my
zoomies and explore.
Can you give me time, patience, love and leadership to grow into being a happy,
confident, loving companion? I sure hope someone will be me a chance!

Interested in adopting Max? Fill out the application here:
https://www.nwboxerrescue.org/adoption-form

If you would like to adopt him, fill out an adoption application on our website www.nwboxerrescue.org

Like us on facebook for more photos of this handsome boy, as well as other boxers we have available! www.facebook.com/northwestboxerrescue

animal.description:
Gabby
8.5 yo female
Fawn
60 pounds
ONLY DOG - NO CATS
Loves her Peeps
Bark Guards if Afraid
Fearful Outside - Needs Socializing
No Crate - Fine when out
Slow Intro to new things
Fostered in Beaverton, OR

Gabby needs a forever friend. Poor little Gabby has not been provided the love, attention, safety and environment needed to relax as a dog. She would bark at a dust bunny if it made noises. Once she realizes no threats are around, she melts into being a love bug. She seems to believe other dogs and the outside world is so scary that nothing can be trusted until she is absolutely certain to be safe. Gabby is going to need slow, deliberately patient, consistent introduction in measured slow increments to release her fear of the unknown, and feel the gentle, loving bond of safety. Inside the home she is a gem. Gabby needs a no dog home, with a person who understands her need to take everything that involves the outside world slowly, not cheating her out of experiences yet providing them in a way she can handle.

Do you have the love, time and patience to give Gabby the stability and time to give you back everything she has tucked in her big heart?

Apply today for Gabby at:

animal.description:
Say hello to Thunder! He is a 2 year old Shepherd mix who weighs 71.7 pounds. Thunder is a big goofball. He is a happy and friendly guy who has lots of energy to burn. 

Thunder needs an adopter who will be committed to training him. Based on what we’ve learned about this guy so far, he would do best with an experienced dog owner. Specifically, someone who has experience training large breed dogs with big personalities. Thunder can be very puppy-like and has not yet learned that jumping, nipping, and being mouthy are unacceptable ways to play with friends. When he gets mouthy, it escalates with excitement - he isn't trying to be aggressive, but this is a behavior that needs to be corrected asap for his safety and the safety of others. We believe that with proper training, these behaviors will be corrected - he just didn't get that training in his life prior to coming to WIsh Bone. Because of his size, energy, and tendency to be mouthy, Thunder will need to go to a family with no kids under the age of 16.

If you'd like to make Thunder a part of your family, please fill out an application to meet him! His minimum adoption fee is $295 plus a $12 fee, if 4 months or older, for rabies registration for McLean County residents. 

He has been neutered, microchipped, vaccinated, heartworm checked, dewormed, and is on flea and heartworm preventatives.

For information about this dog's breed(s), visit: http://www.dogbreedinfo.com/abc.htm 

To fill out our adoption application, go to: http://fs16.formsite.com/WishBoneCanineRescue/adoptionapplication/index.html

animal.description:
Kona is a beautiful 3 year old, Belgian Malinois x Dutch Shepherd who had to say goodbye to her home and brother dog (Kilo also available for adoption through MAD Rescue) due to changing household circumstances.. She's now set out on an amazing journey on her own to find the perfect home! She is up to date on her vaccinations, and is spayed. She is a little shy when she first encounters people and needs to voice her concerns, but she warms up quickly and then, watch out! She's all sorts of playful! She is also a world-class snuggler, kisser, and incredible athlete. This little dynamo can turn on a dime in mid-air to snatch a tennis ball.

Kona has a strong play drive and prey drive. BALL IS LIFE and she also likes to tug. She gets great joy out of wearing her people out! She also is a squirrel chaser, and due to her strong prey drive, we will recommend a home without cats. She gets along with other dogs her own size with proper and gradual introductions, but she likes to be in charge. She has not been tested with unfamiliar small or larger dogs at this time. In her last home, she liked to be the "boss babe," with her dog brother, which sometimes led to nipping and a human needing to step in to break it up. Kona could benefit from learning about appropriate boundries. She has been receptive to children (14 years old and over are a potential), but she is still in the evaluation process at her foster home, and we will post more information as we have the chance to observe her further. Kona is very treat driven and loves her kibble, peanut butter, peaches, apples, and ice cubes! She aims to please and loves her rewards! Kona is skittish with new people, but she is able to take cues from her handler with new experiences. She did well on a trip to Lowe's, and is not spooked by speeding roadbikes, mountain bikes, hikers, or clanging metal. She was appropriately apprehensive when she met a bear, but she did not panic or lunge. 

Kona has not had much training in her past. She's learned "house rules," and has been taught some basic commands (sit, stay, down, come, drop-it), but little else. In foster, we are working on crate training, touch, and manners. She is VERY smart and eager to please. She will need leash training and obedience training, and she'll need a home that is willing to work with her consistently. Kona is mostly potty trained, but will need her training reinforced. She's been known to potty in the house and tear things up when left alone. She is not a fan of her crate and has been known to break out of a wire crate when left alone. Kona will certainly need some time and understanding as she works through her separation anxiety. This girl won't be able to be left alone for long periods of time. A home with adults at home throughout the day will be the best fit for Kona. 

She sure does love her people though and craves belly rubs, cuddles, praise, and attention! Kona will make a great companion for a home that has the time and knowledge to train and encourage her to be the best dog she can be! She is incredibly loving, and will bloom with a family that can give her soft voice and consistent boundaries. Kona has many talents that the right home could develop, and with work, she could excel at agility, flyball, or disc.

If you have questions about Kona, please reach out to her adoption counselor Tarah Winslette Tarah@madrescueinc.org.

If you are interested in adopting Kona, please complete an application at this link https://petstablished.com/adoption_form/24689/generic . 

We are an official 501C3 organization that does not have a physical location. Our home address is in Michigan, however, the majority of our dogs are not located in Michigan. The physical location of each our our dogs is posted with the name of the pet or in the title area. If you are within 4 hours of the pet, please be prepared to pick the pet up. We do provide transport assistance, however, the applicant must drive 50% of the total distance of the transport. 

The information that we have available is in our posting. If you would like to discuss this animal additionally please fill out this application. Applications that are completed in our process and being considered as a match will speak to the foster home to gain more information about our adoptable dog.

animal.description:
Meet Draper!

Draper was found as a stray and taken to Riverside Shelter on December 3rd. He is 8 years old and weighs 82 lbs. At his veterinary exam, we learned Draper is a healthy senior gentleman with arthritis in his front elbows. He doesn't let it stop him from playing fetch - be sure to watch the adorable video!

This handsome guy went on a two week Frosted Fling for the holidays and earned himself a Foster home until he's adopted! Here's what we've learned:

Draper eats kibble like a champ and takes his meds nicely in his breakfast. He longs for you to share what you're eating, but he's very polite and would never impose on you during your meal. Draper is a mellow boy but still enjoys a stroll around the neighborhood. He can walk about 2-3 miles per day in increments and really likes to take in all the smells. Draper is very good with other dogs and kids, but doesn't really know his size and his excitement to say hello can be overwhelming for some. No worries, he calms down to his normal mellow self soon and then gets along with most everyone!

Draper is potty trained, but he only likes to do #2 on walks, not in the yard. Don't worry, he will whimper and let you know it's time to go out!

His Foster Mom shares, "Draper has many lovable qualities:

*

Such a gentleman... always stands up when the lady of the house stands up

*Plays with toys, ropes, and will fetch a ball (you may or may not get it back!)

*Always has his tail wagging when he thinks your going to give him attention.

*Will allow you to sleep 8 hours (no matter what time you go in to sleep)

*Loves belly rubs, ear rubs, all body massage, and cuddles

*Can walk 2-3 miles per day in increments

*Great companion in the car

*Plays well with other dogs

*Great watch /guard dog if he "sees" stranger danger (not sure if he can hear well.)

*Can be trusted to be left alone at home."

Draper is ready for family! Apply at www.frostedfacesfoundation.org/apply

Visit us at Open House: Saturdays & Sundays, 10 am - 1 pm.

Learn more about our programs at www.frostedfacesfoundation.org/family. No adoption fees, and we help with medical costs!

Questions: adopt@frostedfacesfoundation.org

animal.description:
Hi! I'm Anastasia! I am a 4 year old pit/bulldog mix that weighs about 45 lbs, and I'm looking for my Furever home! I am up to date on vaccinations, spayed, and microchipped. I am heartworm positive, but I am undergoing treatment and the rescue pays for treatment until I am heartworm negative! I am house trained, crate trained, and love to run and play outside. I'm currently working on walking on a leash as I tend to pull, but only because I'm so excited to walk. I love belly rubs and will curl up on the couch to watch Netflix, and my foster mom puts on puppy dog pals for me. I love toys, preferably not squeaky ones because I'm not to sure about the sound, but I love chasing a ball. I hardly ever bark but I will let you know when the UPS man is at the door!! I have not been tested with children although I would probably do well with children who are polite and sweet with me. I tend to be picky with my dog friends so I will need to be the one and only, but that's OK because I'm all the dog you'll ever need!

If you are interested in giving Anastasia a forever home, please visit the link below to fill out an application! http://fureverafterrescue.org/adoption-application.html It is best to submit an application through a computer. We have experienced some problems when applications have been submitted using a mobile device. *When you submit the application, you are not obligated to adopt however it does reserve for you the opportunity to adopt that particular animal. We review them on a first come first served basis. If your application is approved, we will contact you and allow you the opportunity to adopt. If you choose not to adopt, we will contact the next approved applicant. If you have any questions or difficulties, please contact us and we will be glad to help!

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.57lbs. | Pit Bull Mix |$400 Adoption FeeBarbara is a sweet 6-year-old, 57-pound Pitbull mix looking to finally find an experienced dog owner that can be her Evergreen family.

Barbara enjoys the spotlight, whether it is tossing a toy around, chewing to the end of a bone, playing co-pilot to her humans on car rides, or being a funny girl working on her barrel rolls around the home. She can read her audience when it comes to dogs or humans and plays off their energy level meaning if she is surrounded by bustle she can get rowdy, and if surrounded by a calmer home will mirror the calmer energy.

Barbara is constantly rehearsing her leash manners for the main event of a walk and will need to continue to work on this in her forever home. At first, her over-exuberance can intimidate other dogs, but with slow introductions she does well. She loves time with other dogs, where she can say Hello Dolly (or Donny) to canine companions. We may know the story of The Owl and The Pussycat, but the story of Barbara and the feline friend is not a good counterpart, so she should not go to a home with cats. Barbara has not yet been around children, but due to her mirroring the energy of those around her, it would be best for her to go to a calmer home with middle school age children or above.

Barbara was born a star, and after a rough start has decided no more tears and that she is ready to meet the family of her dreams. You don't have to bring this girl flowers, but bones to win her affection. Apply to meet Barbara at https://rescuecrew.org/adopt-animal-in-need/#adoptionapplication

The adoption fee covers the cost of the animal's spay/neuter surgery, microchipping, FIV/FeLK testing (for cats) or Heartworm Testing (for dogs), deworming and all core age appropriate vaccinations. For the most complete information regarding this animal, and all of our adoptable pets, please ensure you are visiting our website directly at www.RescueCrew.org. You can also access the necessary online adoption application here as well. Thank you.

animal.description:
This is Rooney!

8-year-old Rooney was brought into the Riverside Shelter as over-the-counter stray. He weighs 6 lbs. A visit to our vet revealed that he has some kidney issues, but luckily. his heart sounds and looks great, so we can treat him! Rooney has dental surgery scheduled in February.

On January 16th, Rooney landed himself a wonderful Foster home. His Foster Mom asked who has been overlooked and who really needed her. Rooney looked up with his one eye and asked if he could be the lucky one she chose, and he was! Rooney desperately wants to be loved! He will walk up to volunteers in the yard and wait to be noticed. He doesn't enjoy being picked up (that's where blankets come in handy!), but if you sit near him, he will climb into your lap and nudge you for pets. We look forward to hearing how Rooney blossoms in his Foster home.

We received a great first update from Rooney's Foster Mom! She shared, "Checking in after Rooney's first week in foster. Rooney is a HUGE cuddle bug. Anywhere you are sitting he will come and sit next to you, on top of you, one paw touching, or head on your lap, he will come as close as you allow. He doesn't know what personal space means. If I let him, he would sleep on my face! He would love nothing more than to have someone pet him ALL day. I was warned that he wasn't a fan of being picked up, but we haven't had that problem at all! He seems a little unsure but has never reacted to being picked up. The only time he has reacted is when he is being groomed. He doesn't like grooming and will let you know. He can be melodramatic about it. But despite the occasional snarkiness when being groomed (and to be fair, few dogs enjoy grooming), Rooney is the sweetest boy. He doesn't hold grudges. 30 seconds after snarking at me for grooming him, he is back on my lap rolling around and pawing at me for pets. I call him my little sour patch kid. First he's sour, then he's sweet. Very very sweet!"

Check back soon for the next update on Rooney! If you think this cuddle bug might be the one for you, apply to meet him: www.frostedfacesfoundation.org/apply

Visit us at Open House: Saturdays & Sundays, 10 am - 1 pm

Learn more about our programs at www.frostedfacesfoundation.org/family. No adoption fees, and we help with medical costs!

Questions: adopt@frostedfacesfoundation.org

They do not come much more stunning than Noble. Like blue eyes or brown? No need to choose-he has one of each! He is just a gorgeous boy and is as charming as he is good looking.
Noble is a young boy and it is pretty clear that he did not get much training in his previous home. He is very active and pretty wild right now, but we have no doubt he'll settle in to a very nice well behaved boy after getting some clear, concise and consistent training. We are looking for a Siberian savvy home for him and he is really not a great starter husky just yet. No young kids at this point until he gets some calmer manners. We want someone with experience who can be a confident leader and who is active and can take him out for jogs or perhaps bike riding. He would require a 6' fence as he can leap pretty high. He is very athletic!
Noble likes other dogs but can play rough so he is not a good choice for littler dogs or seniors. An active female would be his ideal playmate. He is such a diamond in the rough and spending a bit of time training him will result in a wonderful companion.

********************************************

Joey: What if you saw a three-legged puppy?
Chandler: I'd be sad, sure - but I wouldn't cry.
Joey: OK; well, what if the puppy said, "Help me, Chandler. All the other puppies pick on me"?
Chandler: Cry? I just found a talking puppy! I'm rich!

We received the most informative email about a dog who needed us, from the dog herself. Although we know the dog didn’t type it-man that coulda made LEAD get rich fo real-we said yes to helping before finishing the email. 

It stated she was found shivering and a nice human took her in. This human-who btw seems to know the secrets of rescue pretty well-posted all over with flyers, contacting local vets, checking for a chip, etc to get this beaut back home. But nothing came about, so this dog had to figure out another plan. She visited the park’s local pee messages left on fire hydrants and unlucky bushes about what to do and butt sniffed out the 5 star “Yelp” reviews about LEAD. This is a smart coming of age dog, I’m telling ya.

And now I will be a dog to describe Sparrow because how fun.

My name is Sparrow and I am a 7-8 year old, 70-80 lb Doberman Hound mix. I honestly have no idea where my original family went but I guess I have to move on to finding someone completely new. Someone who will love me unconditionally and grow attached to my old soul. I settle pretty quickly in a new environment especially if you enjoy toys as much as me. I love to carry mine around in my mouth, but doubt you do since you have hands. I don’t mess with anything in the home and that includes no potty messes either. A lady never poops where she eats! I do fine with other dogs as long as we get a proper intro so don’t just put your big booty in my face. I currently live with a small dog and she wants to play but I rather sleep the day away. I’m mildly playful but still nap city sounds so much better than play city. However, I love going on quarantine walks any time of the day since there’s literally nothing else to do. I like to be the “LEADer” hehe, so my foster human got me a head halter to help with my “leading” the way. I know a lot of basic commands being so treat motivated, so therefore someone did take the time with me at some point. However, you’ll need to keep teaching me to use my soft jowls instead of my strong teeth to take these delicious treats. I’m just too excited for food! I’m not at all a huge barker but if I hear a disturbing noise at home. I might have to chime in. But to be honest, you’ll probably enjoy me scaring away robbers and creeps. Although I think just seeing me, they wouldn’t dare try. Maybe have them feed me a treat with my hard mouth lol. And lastly, no cats or kids for me, please. I’m a senior who just wants to sunker down without having to be bothered by grubby little paws or bothered by your two year old’s tantrums.

If you are interested in our non talking dog but like a normal dog, please apply for Sparrow at leadrescue.org!
