animal.description:
Mitzi's video: https://youtu.be/VjuKWgpNQLA

Name: Mitzi
Age: 7 yrs
Sex: Female
Previous Life:
Weight: 20 lbs and on a diet
Altered: Yes
Housebroken: Working on it!
Good with dogs/cats/kids: Yes and will need another dog/s in the home/Unnknown/Unknown
Dislikes: Sudden movements and loud noises tend to scare her
Crate trained: Working on it!
Fenced yard required: Yes

Special Needs:

- Mitzi is very prone to sores between her toes and she needs weekly epsom salt bath soaks for her paws
- Dry Eye & PK – she doesn’t see out of her right eye very well, maybe shadows if up close. She gets lube in both eyes 3-4 times a day and Optimune 1 time a day in both eyes.
- Because of her poor vision, Mitzi has poor depth perception and cannot go down stairs (she can go up them). A home with no stairs, or with a family who is willing to always carry her down any stairs is required.
 
Favorite Toys – doesn’t play with any dog toys – but loves towels & clothes. If she has a towel to play with or to steal from you she is a happy girl. 
She’s not playful with me or my dogs. She’s playful with towels, clothes, paper, leaves, grass, and everything she finds that a dog shouldn’t have. 

Favorite Activity - Snoozing on the bed or playing with a towel or clothes. She wants to be where everyone is and cries to let us know she wants to be included.

Favorite treat – Keifer Milk (frozen into bone shape); almost climbs in the freezer for one!

Hi! My name is Mitzi and I’m a 7 year old apricot pug. I’ve been learning how to become a family pet and I’ve been having a lot of fun! I’m learning that love from a human is amazing! I absolutely love getting belly rubs and I demand them often.

My mom says I’m “skittish” because I’m still unsure of sudden movements so I tend to freeze in place out of fear. However, I love sleeping in bed with my foster mom, foster fur brother, and foster fur sister. I also love my foster mom’s towels and clothes. I’m ornery so I like to steal them, take off running with them so my foster mom has to chase me.
 
I’m looking for a forever home that is patient with me. I’m working on weight loss so that will be important to continue. My eyes are dry and need medicine a couple of times a day. I do have allergies so I need medicine when they are bad. I also need a home that has a fenced in yard with another dog who I can follow around & learn from. I haven’t been around cats or kids but since I’m still unsure of sudden movements I’d probably do best with older children or dog savvy children.
 
I’m a fun, ornery and sassy pug looking for a house that is patient and likes to have fun.
 
Mitzi’s minimum adoption donation is $275.

Interested in adopting? Email our adoption coordinator kristi@pugpartners.com and let her know why you think your home is a perfect match for Mitzi!

animal.description:
Hi I am Jenni, an 8 year old 65 pound pit mix. I have had a rough start to life and am learning what life is like inside a home and I absolutely love it!   My favorite thing to do is run and play with balls. I have not quite learned the concept of bringing the ball back though, and I love to find some great hiding spots throughout the yard.  Cow ears are my favorite treat but I am not a picky eater so I will try just about anything.  I forgot to mention that I just LOVE toys but they do not stand a chance around me! I know some basic commands and I am learning leash manners.  I am also house and crate trained and get along great with all of my humans. I am dog selective so I would like to meet other dogs before coming home if I am not the only dog. I have a high prey drive, so cats and I do not get along very well. After running and playing, I love snuggling up in a nice blanket and getting some love and rubs!  I am now looking for my forever family, one that will love me and give me the home I know I deserve! 

Are you interested in adopting Jenni or another JCAPL pet you have seen? You'll need to start by completing an adoption application, available online at our website: www.jcapl.org. There is no obligation to adopt by completing an application, however, we do recommend submitting an application as soon as you find an animal you are interested in. We review applications in the order they are received.

Completed applications can be sent via email to adopt@jcapl.org , faxed to 919-300-5524 or delivered in person by visiting us at one of our adoption events on Saturdays at PetSmart in Garner (White Oak Shopping Center). 

We will contact you as soon as possible once we receive your application.

Thanks for thinking adoption!

animal.description:
See more pictures of Popcorn and her entire story on her Facebook album!
https://www.facebook.com/media/set/?vanity=forgottendogsrescue&set=a.3677031172315653

Our special girl Popcorn is finally ready to find her forever home! 

Popcorn came to us in October as a 3-month-old pup with a fractured elbow. She had emergency surgery at WSU vet school to repair her elbow, then needed a second surgery two months later to remove the plates once the fracture had healed. Additionally, she also had a mast cell tumor on her head that was removed when she was spayed.
Popcorn was born in July 2020, so she is now a little over 6 months old, is a bulldog, and she weighs about 40 pounds. 

This sweet and sassy nugget is feisty, silly, snuggly, and a very social girl with a BIG personality!  She loves going out in public and meeting all the people to get all the love!
Popcorn has been well socialized and loves everyone, canine and human.  She thinks going to the vet is a social event!  Everyone she greets gets a wiggle and a snort.  Such a funny girl!

Popcorn is working on potty training and her adopter will need to continue working on that, and general puppy training, with her.  She’s learned to tell her foster mom when she needs to go outside, and she is very treat motivated. She is crate trained, but when she wants out of her crate she will let you know, and let you know LOUDLY. Popcorn lives with canine foster brothers and cats.  She loves them all but will chase the cats if allowed so, while she can live with kitties, it needs to be kitties who are dog savvy and will ignore a silly pup.  She definitely has a more dominant and bossy personality with other dogs, and she’s a very physical, robust player. If there's another dog in the home, it should be a male.
She has been around kids and while she’s done great with them, we don’t recommend she live in a home with small children (12 or over) because she can be mouthy, especially if touched in a way she doesn’t like (her elbow required physical therapy and she made her opinions clear about not liking that!). 

Popcorn loves all toys and loves to play.  When playing by herself she somersaults -- tosses the toy and then starts rolling around.  And has an extraordinary snore when sleeping!  Life is grand and Popcorn goes full on in everything she loves -- playing, snuggling, snoring -- you get the idea!  And when she isn’t happy about something she has quite a scream.  Yes, scream. Her foster mom has nicknamed her the “mandrake root” (Harry Potter reference!) because she makes her opinions very known. 

While Popcorn’s elbow has healed as well as could be expected given the fracture, she will always have a slight limp and arthritis will definitely develop in that elbow. She’ll need to be kept on life-long joint supplements, an NSAID (eg carprofen), and kept at a lean weight. Since she needs to be on NSAIDs long term, she should have, at minimum, yearly bloodwork. Continued physical therapy and acupuncture would also benefit her elbow. 
An adopter will also need to prepared for the possibility of Popcorn developing additional mast cell tumors, as it isn’t typically common for a pup so young to have had one. The one she had was removed with clean margins and was low-grade, and she hasn’t developed any more, but an adopter will need to keep an eye on her for any possible growths.

We would prefer an adopter who is familiar with or has had experience with English bulldogs.

If you think Popcorn would be a good addition to your home please complete an application, which can be downloaded from our website www.forgottendogsrescue.com. Her adoption fee is $450, and she has been spayed, is up to date with vaccinations, and microchipped.

animal.description:
This very handsome long-legged Pyrenees boy is Bear, and he is a sweetheart! Bear loves people, he is sweet and smart and so lucky to be in rescue now. Bear ended up with a lousy owner who let him roam his entire life. He was not cared for and rarely fed. He was finally taken in by a Good Samaritan who contacted the owner who did not even want him back. Bear is a little shy because he has not had a lot of socialization, but so sweet. Remarkably, he is house trained and did fantastic with all of the dogs in his temporary home. Kindly, they reached out to rescue for help with him as he turned out to be heartworm positive. He is being treated for that now with the slow kill method and should make a full recovery. Bear is so happy to have regular meals and people paying attention to him for once. Although a very sweet boy he will sometimes emit a low growl around the food bowl around the other dogs, but this is probably since he went without food for so long. We are not sure if he is ever been around cats but he did well when he met a cat in boarding. Bear will need an understanding foster or adopter who will work with him to teach him everything he needs to know. He does well on leash and he is neutered. He loves to play with other dogs both big and small. He is a young boy and he was especially fond of a smaller bouncy female dog who lived with the folks who found him. We don't think he had ever lived indoors before but he did remarkably well and couldn't wait to go into the house with the other dogs and hang out with people. Bear is a great boy who needs a kind person to teach him the ropes. He will make a great dog for some lucky owner. He can be a bit shy in new situations, but warms up quickly when he is shown kindness. He deserves much better than he has known so far and we are all thankful he is safe in rescue!

NYS Registered Rescue # RR102
View full listing, fee and online application at - www.nationalpyr.org/adoptable-dogs (sorry, no phone submissions, but if you would like more information you can email us at renpyrgroup@yahoo.com).

Secure VISIBLE fencing is required; invisible fencing WILL NOT contain this breed.

Our goal is to assess every application on its own merits. Key considerations are: 1) the experience of the applicant with large breed dogs 2) children in the household or regularly visiting the household are ready for a large-breed dog who is a guardian by nature (www.nationalpyr.org/know-the-breed) and 3) the sex of other dogs currently residing in the household to avoid same-sex aggression issues. For puppies under six months old, the applicant’s ability to socialize the puppy with older dogs is a priority.

animal.description:
Sweet Darla now! Bottom right is Darla before coming to the shelter.

Darla and he friend Prince came to the shelter together from a cruelty case. Poor Prince was trapped on a chain without food, water or proper shelter and was slowly starving to death.  Darla had escaped her chain and was able to scrounge the area for what she could find, but she didn't abandon her buddy Prince! Thankfully someone noticed their condition and called the Baldwin County Animal Shelter to request a welfare check. The AC officer was able to confiscate both of the dogs from this heartbreaking situation and bring them to the safety of the shelter. Yes, the owner WAS charged! A couple short months later, they're healthy and ready for adoption!! 

Darla is approximately 4 years old and 60-65 pounds. Darla is a very sweet and loving girl that seems to be good with all other dogs. She LOVES to play with her buddies in the play yard, but she loves to stop for affection from her humans just as much! Darla and Prince are *not* bonded and do not need to be adopted together. During her time at the shelter, Darla has realized there's more to life than being pursued by male dogs while she was just trying to survive. And our silly Prince doesn't always have great manners when it comes to showing his love of the ladies. ?????

Adoption fee: $150; includes spay or neuter, vaccinations (dhlpp and rabies), deworming for intestinal parasites and flea treatment. Heartworm test (including first 30 days of prevention) can be added for an additional $20.

Rescue inquiries can be sent to Friendsofbcacga@gmail.com or you can call the shelter directly at 478-445-5514 and leave a voicemail for a call back from the Rescue and Adoption Coordinator.

The Baldwin County Animal Shelter is often operating at capacity, this means that for every dog or cat that comes in, another must leave via rescue or adoption, or risk being euthanized for space.  Multiple dogs and cats come to the shelter EVERY DAY, which means animals must also be moving out at the same rate. Unfortunately, sometimes there are larger adult, "pitbull" or mix-breed dogs that are continually overlooked for their younger or more "adoptable" counterparts. Please consider adopting a new best friend today!

Are you a Pyr lover? Hound lover? Good dog lover? Well look no further...meet Casey! Casey is a loveable Pyr (possibly) basset hound mix who is looking for a family to shower him with love! Casey is a good boy who is working hard to Pyrfect his basic commands. He is house trained and has good recall. He loves to meet new people and play with his canine buddies. Casey loves most things including his toys, belly rubs and food...all food :) He’s very food motivated especially when there is cheese or peanut butter involved. Casey is very sensitive to things around his neck, which may be a result of some past trauma, so he prefers to use his harness when he goes on walks. He does well with kids but would prefer a home with older human siblings who will understand his sensitivity around his neck. Casey is looking for a medium energy home with lots of love to give. He has never met a stranger and is very submissive to his furry friends. He is a goofy, loveable boy who loves to lay on his tummy with his legs straight out to cool off! Casey will make the Pyrfect addition to any loving home - apply for this sweet boy today!

to adopt or ask questions:
https://dogs2ndchance.org/

Hi, I'm Reese! I'm a 5 year old lab mix who just loves to have fun! I'm pretty small for my age, but that doesn't stop me from having a good time. If you get me toys, no matter what they are, I want em! They keep me occupied, but most of all, I just wanna chill with you in your lap all day. I'm just looking for a loving home that will give me the life I've never had! My fosters love and adore me, and I know you will, too! Reese has what we think is a condition called vitiligo. This condition is not uncomfortable and not something that has to be medicated or managed. It is just a loss of pigment in the skin, causing discoloration. Reese is happy, healthy, and very much enjoying a normal life!
Thank you for considering adopting a new family member.

Memphis area adoption fee is
$200

All dogs are spayed or neutered {unless medical issues prohibit the surgery}, up to date on vaccinations, microchipped, heartworm tested {if old enough} and treated if necessary. They also are de-wormed and start heartworm and flea prevention when rescued. It is continued until adopted. Adopter is furnished with their 1st month's heartworm prevention.

**
Out of State adoption fee is
$425
and includes a

$150.00 the non refundable transportation fee paid to an approved animal transportation company.

Several states require the dog to be quarantined 48 hours before pickup.
The adopter pays the quarantine fee at time of pick up. Unless otherwise indicated

Your Adoption Fee Includes

Microchip

Spay or Neuter

All age appropriate vaccinations

* Local 2 week trial adoption

Adopter's first Month's Heartworm prevention

2 week supply of food to transition to your brand of food.

Known Medical Issues are addressed before Adoption; Any Other Issues are Disclosed

**

animal.description:
Hey everyone! My name is Pop, I am somewhere between 5 and 7 years. I weigh in at about 85 pounds, I am not a small pup, but I am still a lap dog if you let me be! My previous owner did one of those fancy DNA tests and it says I am a Staffordshire terrier mix, all I know is I have a hard head, a great personality, a goofy smile and I love treats!
 
Originally I came to Louie's Legacy due to hurricane Harvey down in Houston. After a bit of time with my foster family, I found a new forever home with an awesome guy who loved to take me on long walks and give me endless love and snuggles. Sadly, he passed away in August so my original foster family stepped right back up to take me back so I would be with familiar people. Well, now I am back and available again, I do have a few eccentricities though. 
 
I do not like wooden floors, they scare me. I try sometimes, and I have been making great strides with my foster family since they have a huge wooden floor in their house,  maybe you can help me get over that fear. I also have a bit of a bad habit of guarding my food and toys, not all of the time, but that means I can be a bit unpredictable once in a while, so it is best if I go to a home with no other animals that might upset me if they took my food or toys. It is also a good idea if I am not in a home with kids under 13. I like kids, but they pull on my tail or tug my ears or hurt me and take my stuff, and sometimes I just don't like that and I let them know, and it gets me in trouble. 
 
So, if you have a comfy home with carpets or at least not all wood floors, no other pets so I can have all of your love, no little kids under 13 and want a puppers that will show you endless love and attention, then let's talk. My foster family loves me to death, I even sleep at the foot of their bed every night, but they feel I deserve a forever home, maybe you can be the one to make that a reality for me. 
 
I look forward to meeting you, and you falling madly in love with me. 
 
Sincerely,
Pop                                                                                                                                                                               PS-my adoption fee is $250.

To adopt this pet, please visit https://www.louieslegacy.org/adopt

All of our dogs come spayed or neutered, fully up to date on vaccinations, including rabies (if age appropriate) and bordetella, are microchipped, heartworm negative, current on flea/tick and heartworm prevention, dewormed, and treated for any ailments found upon veterinary examination. The adoption fee covers a portion of these services, and makes it possible for us to continue rescuing animals.  

For more information on the adoption fees and the adoption process, please complete our adoption application here: https://www.louieslegacy.org/adopt - an application allows us to get to know your family better so we can assess whether the animal you are interested in is a good match for your home. An application does not obligate you to adopt. Please understand that due to the volume of applications some animals receive, we are unable to contact all applicants. If your application is considered a good fit for the dog you are interested in, or even a different pet, a volunteer will give you a call as soon as possible.  

We are a foster based rescue and do not have a shelter location where dogs can be seen during the week. Please see our Facebook page at https://www.facebook.com/LouiesLegacy for our weekly adoption album if you are interested in meeting a dog in person. Not all animals attend every adoption event, please check our Facebook page for animal event times and locations before you make a trip to meet a specific animal.

Thanks so much for caring about a needy animal!

animal.description:
With her stunning golden, reddish coat, Poni is looking for an active home where she can accompany you on a daily walk/run and all your Colorado outdoor activities. Pony is medium to high energy and will do best in a home with a fenced yard where she will have space to play and run. Poni loves to run in the play yard and is large so she will need a good size fenced yard. She has been friendly with the other doggies and kids in her foster home but does not do well with alpha females. She would probably be happy as an only dog where she can receive all of person's attention. This pretty girl is about 1 year old, spayed, and weighs a hefty 85 lbs according to her foster. We think she is a golden/lab retriever mix.

If you are interested in adopting, please complete an application at https://www.circle2rescue.com/dog-adoption-application/ The adoption fee of $250 includes the spay/neuter, vaccinations, deworming and microchip. 

Please note, Circle 2 Rescue cannot guarantee the breed, composition or ages of our dogs as we usually have no history prior to them entering the rescue. We make every effort to ensure the dogs are healthy.

animal.description:
Update: Georgia was fostered for a short period of time by a lovely couple with dog experience and here is what they had to say: She is a woman's only dog. Extremely skittish around men. When approached with harness and a leash she will growl and nip and cannot be bribed even with treats. She may never learn to walk on leash and just be happy as a couch potato. She followed the woman everywhere she went inside and out. She does go outside to do her business and on a potty pad. She likes to sleep and cuddle in bed under the blankets. *** The rescue believes with paitence and understanding and time that all things are possible. She seems to hang back while on leash to be able to see what you are doing. We are happy to offer the support of our trainer and find Georgia a more suitable home. These people really NEEDED a dog that had leash manners and that is ok. This is why we let peopel foster. 

Georgia O'Keefe is from our Artist Family. She is almost 2 years old. She came from a "not so nice home" and adjusting well. Georgia needs a home that is rather calm and someone is home most of the time. She needs someone with time and patience to help her gain confidence and trust with people. Once she knows you, she becomes a happy, friendly girl. She needs a person of family to show her love, how to be a dog, and and to take her on fun adventures. Goergia O'Keefe once said, "I've been absolutely terrified every moment of my life - and I've never let it keep me from doing a single thing I wanted to do." Our georgia has a slight underbite and it makes her a little self conscious, but to us it is actually adorable especially when she smiles. If you are looking for a new addition to your family and have the time and patience to give a dog a second chance at happiness, then make an appointment to meet our girl, Georgia O'Keefe.

Adoption fees include: Spay or Neuter, All vaccinations are up to date, and a microchip. If you have current pets we do allow a two week trial period for $25. This allows us to make sure that the animal will fit in with the resident animals.

Come meet me!
We would like people to fill out our pre-application form here: https://forms.gle/uLhPh6h8Ghg73TRt6
Once these forms are reviewed, we will contact you to make an appointment for an in person meet and greet. We are doing our best to be fair and work with our limited staff and rescources. 
Countryside Rescue is open by appointment.

Hi I'm Valentina, I'm a sweet girl hoping to find my new forever home. I have been staying in shelters for a long time so I'm hoping yours will be the one that sticks. I am good on the leash (I love a harness), sweet - playful and a bundle of fun. Come and meet me today. I will need to be the only fur child in the house. Did I mention I know all my basic commands and then some, and I am very potty trained. I am a super intelligent lady. I would also do best in a home with no young children, as it can sometimes take me a little time to build trust with new people. I hope to make your acquaintance soon! 

My adoption fee is now fully waived thanks to a generous sponsor! 

I'm currently in a foster! If you'd like to meet with me please reach out to my foster at (928) 380-6338!

Bonus Perks of Adopting a Foster Dog:
- Extra time spent working on potty training!
- Insider info, like how I do being home alone and what I'm like at night!
- Extra training time given to house manners, like greeting visitors!
- My foster can give you tips on all my favorite things and least favorite things!

animal.description:
Rocky is a handsome, well-behaved fella that loves to spend time with our volunteers! He's a pittie/terrier type mix, approximately 65 pounds. Rocky walks great on a leash, sits and shakes on cue and knows basic commands. He keeps his kennel clean and is possibly house trained as well. But since he came in as a stray and was never reclaimed, we do not know his history or background. Unfortunately we do know that someone cropped Rocky's ears extremely short at some point, but we still think he's adorable!

Rocky is a really good boy, that would do well in most any household! (Any dog can be tested with cats upon request.)

Adoption fee: $150; includes spay or neuter, vaccinations (dhlpp and rabies), deworming for intestinal parasites and flea treatment. Heartworm test (including first 30 days of prevention) can be added for an additional $20.

Rescue inquiries can be sent to Friendsofbcacga@gmail.com or you can call the shelter directly at 478-445-5514 and leave a voicemail for a call back from the Rescue and Adoption Coordinator.

The Baldwin County Animal Shelter is often operating at capacity, this means that for every dog or cat that comes in, another must leave via rescue or adoption, or risk being euthanized for space.  Multiple dogs and cats come to the shelter EVERY DAY, which means animals must also be moving out at the same rate. Unfortunately, sometimes there are larger adult, "pitbull" or mix-breed dogs that are continually overlooked for their younger or more "adoptable" counterparts. Please consider adopting a new best friend today!

animal.description:
***Before reading about Nova please understand that she will NOT be adopted out to a home without a fenced-in backyard.****

Miss Nova is a 4 year old petite mastiff who had made huge strides in the year she has been in foster and is finally available for adoption. Overall she can be summed up as a goofy couch potato and serious snuggle bug. She LOVES going on walks but since she does react to other dogs she needs to be muzzled at ALL times when she is outside without a fence. Miss Nova is completely muzzle trained and doesnt miss a beat when putting it on and struts her stuff while wearing it.

From her foster:
- She is an absolutely perfect passsenger in the vehicle; she just sits in the front seat and chills on rides.
- She likes to nap on the couch or on her dog bed in my bedroom. 
- She loves squeaker toys and her benebone.
- She likes playing fetch but doesn’t release the ball very well lol. Kinda gotta pry it out of her mouth. But she doesn’t get aggressive when you go for it.
-She stays in her room at night that her kennel is in when I go to sleep.
-She gets apprehensive when mail carriers/delivery drivers show up so I just keep her in her room with the door closed when I leave for work/errands.
-When Nova meets new people in my home I have her sit and hold onto her collar when they walk in. I tell the person to talk so she can hear their voice and then I let her go and she’s all about pets and violent tail wags. :)

*To meet Miss Nova please complete the link below for our adoption application. A meet-and-greet will NOT be scheduled until your application is approved*

animal.description:
Meet Shadow, he is a lab mix weighing about 30 lbs. 3 yrs. old.
As you can see has only one eye, He was beat by some awful people. He does just fine with one eye though and has no more pain. Shadow had all his shots, and is neutered. 
He is ok on leash but enjoys off leash walks very much. And has great recall . 
What you can’t train he has lots of, unconditional love, desire to please, wants to play with all other dogs, nonstop wagging tail, loves to cuddle.
If I could read his mind I know what he is thinking when he first wakes up. Smile on his face, tail wagging, happy vibe.
This is awesome I get to spend another day with my human.
Yes, Shadow has had a rough go. Has been dealt some bad cards along the way but his spirit and joy are contagious and never ending. He holds no grudge and his ability to forgive is a lesson to all.
If you are the kind person that has been knocked down a few times, been kicked by people who were supposed to love you but you wake up every day with a bounce in your step and a kind hello to everyone you meet then you have may have just found your forever sidekick in Shadow.
If you can find the space in your heart to get to know this walking, tail wagging angel, I would like you to meet him.

animal.description:
NorthStar is looking for an adoptive home for Rosebud.  She is currently in foster care in Coon Rapids, MN.  She is a spayed female about 4.5 years old.  Her main care taker passed away and the other is not able to physically care for a Great Pyrenees.  She is housetrained and somewhat leash trained, but not crate trained.  Rosebud is a big girl at about 98 pounds.  Rosebud prefers to get all the attention from her people and needs to be an only dog.  It is unknown how she does with cats, but likely best in a cat free home.  She may be too excitable for younger children.  She is not bothered by loud noises and is wary of strangers at first (she is a Pyr!).  She will dig in the yard if looking for mice or toads!!  If not contained by secure, visible fencing, Rosebud WILL go walkabout.  Rosie is a failed livestock guardian and needs to be an indoor family pet.

Rosie is spayed and up to date on shots.  Secure, visible fencing is almost always needed or adopt from NorthStar.  

If you are interested in adopting Rosebud, an adoption application, site visit, secure visible fencing, and an adoption fee are required.

animal.description:
Landon is a cute adorable fluff-ball of love. He's gregarious, an instigator and will run circles around your other dogs. He likes to sleep in bed with his foster mom and will calm down after about a half hour to go to sleep. He hates to be crated. He is up to date on his shots and microchipped heartworm negative and weighs about 13 lb. He just got groomed and was a very good boy for the groomer. Landon was surrendered by his owner because they were moving. Landon needs a home where he knows that he won't be discarded.  He will follow you everywhere, and loves to be with his people.  He knows how to sit and is housetrained.  He learned the doggy door immediately - very smart little boy!  No small children under the age of 12.  Landon tends to nip when he's happy and excited - he will nip human legs if they are running.  It's not a mean bite, at all but it does hurt!  He just needs to learn boundaries, especially with other dogs.  He plays very rough and could potentially hurt a tiny dog.  After being in his foster home a few weeks, we are now thinking Landon would do best as as an only dog, or with another dog his size who also loves to play rough.

Alcovy dogs are spayed/neutered, up to date on all vaccines, up to date on heart-worm preventative and flea preventative and micro-chipped.  Required registration of microchip in owner's name is $11.99.

This adorable dog is Diesel and he is hoping for a home in time for the holidays.  Diesel is 3.5 years old and about 60 lbs. He is very loving with people and a total cutie. He is a Rottweiler mix.

We have not had him around young children but would be fine with older kids.

animal.description:
Cable is a 2-year-old Pit Bull Terrier mix who weighs 60 pounds. His number one goal in life is to give love to every human he meets and he is an amazing Couch-Snuggler! He enjoys long walks and is training nicely in puppy manners (sit, down, stay, and leave it). In the house he can get a little mouthy during game time and until that is corrected, we recommend homes with older children. He is also working on leash reactivity (loud yelping and lunging at other leashed dogs barking at him). His reactivity is not aggressive, it is just that he was not appropriately socialized on leash walks. He sleeps and takes his meals without issue in his crate and gets along with other dog in foster home. We do not know how he is with cats.

If you are interested in adopting Cable please submit an inquiry directly with Greater Charlotte SPCA by visiting charlottespca.org/adopt.

***Because our rescue is composed entirely of volunteers and we require a home check for each of our adoptable pets prior to them going to their new homes, local applications will take precedence. We will accept out of town applications, but any family further than 60 miles from Charlotte is responsible for finding a representative of a rescue local to them that is willing to perform the home check. All out of town applicants will also have to be willing to drive to Charlotte to meet/pick up the pet as soon as the application is approved.***

animal.description:
Thank you for your interest in dog who needs a new home. Adoption can be one of the most fulfilling experiences in your life and especially in the life of your new canine companion.

A note to those looking at CPR. We have no perfect dogs - but many of our dogs have proven to be perfect for a certain someone. Our job is to find those someone's. Our most successful adopters come to CPR not because they want a dog. They come to us because they want to give a dog a home. We urge all of our potential adopters not to fall in love with a picture. While we like to know what you like in looks, a dog is more than a pretty face. Our goal is to match you with the best possible pet for you and your home. We want to create furever families.

Our descriptions contain all that we know about this dog today. We'll update as more information is known.

Are you looking to adopt within the next 30 days? If so please visit our webpage at www.carolinapoodlerescue.org and complete the application. You'll find it in the menu on the left hand side. You'll also find a total listing of all our dogs available.

Just browsing but interested in poodles and poodle mixes? Please drop a note to applications@carolinapoodlerescue.org with your name, address and phone # and email. We'll add you to our mailing list.

thanks
the CPR Adoption team

Date into Rescue: 11/17/20
Reason for being in rescue: Owner release/owner going into assisted living
Foster location: Dreamweaver Farms, Pacolet SC
Special Needs? Addy is highly allergic to fleas - she must have good flea control year round. She may also have other allergies. Her new family will watch her carefully for seasonal or food related changes and adjust accordingly. Addy was spayed and had a dental polishing on 11/27/20. She is now ready for her forever home. ADDY DOES SHED.
Weight: 9.3 lb
Height: 10 in
Spayed/Neutered: Yes

Adoption Fee: $349

Fence needed? No

What kind of home would be best for me? Addy is accustomed to a stay at home person and she misses that. Addy's forever home has someone at home during the day (work-from-home family, home-school family, etc.). She is a young, active dog who is looking for a more active than lazy lifestyle. Addy can be needy and wants your undivided attention. She can be a little testy when other dogs enter her space. Given this, she is best suited to be the only dog in her forever home.

Addy is looking for a family that that will see past her sometimes shy exterior for the heart this girl is looking to give her family. Addy does shed.

What is my personality like? Friendly and sweet, Addy is longing for a home again. She loves to climb up into our bedding storage areas and find a soft spot to snuggle down in. The job Addy wants is BFF. She is a happy, affectionate and loving little girl who years for a family of her own. Her goal in life is to be your best friend, your go-to girl, the one you want to spend time with.

Addy can bee shy in her own way. She is not a dog that we see doing sports or even being a therapy dog. Though she can be shy, when she's with family, with those she loves, she's everything you're looking for and a family pet. She is energetic, playful, and loves to be held and cuddled. Addy is food motivated - and can get quite vocal about meal times.

How do I act when I first meet new people? Friendly

Other tips and tidbits: We do not know Addy's exact birthdate but her owner thinks she is about 5 years old. We've given Addy the birthdate of 11/15/15 based on this information.

House trained? Dogs can be house trained if they are in the right environment and are allowed to follow a schedule as long as a physical reason doesn't keep them from being trained. A dog house trained in my home may not be in yours. We will help you teach your new dog this necessary skill and based on your schedule.

Please note - we do not ship dogs. If you are interested in adopting, please take a look at the distance between the foster home location and your location and make sure you are willing to make that trip. Most of our dogs are at our farm in Pacolet, South Carolina.

To apply, please visit our webpage at www.carolinapoodlerescue.org and visit the tab on the left that directions you to the online application.

Please note that when screening applications, we look at the entire home and then make suggestions based on what would be a good fit for your home. You are not being screened for a specific dog although we are looking to see what type of dog interests you - poodles or non poodles, color, age, etc. Others here may be a better fit for you. It is very difficult to get to know a living animal from a picture and a short description. Since we are constantly getting in new dogs, this may be a dog not in our listings yet. We want you to be very happy with your new companion and will make suggestions based on what you tell us about you.

Thank you for considering CPR.

PLEASE NOTE PETFINDER INQUIRES ARE NOT BEING RECEIVED email INFO@GOLDENHUGGS.ORG with your questions. 


PLEASE READ THE REQUIREMENTS IN FULL BEFORE APPLYING!

THE NEEDS OF YOUNG DOGS FOR EXERCISE AND COMPANIONSHIP CAN GENERALLY NOT BE FILLED WHEN FAMILIES ARE GONE A LARGE  PART OF THE DAY.  APPLICATIONS WHERE YOUNG DOGS ARE LEFT LONG HOURS WILL NOT BE CONSIDERED .

PLEASE KEEP IN MIND THESE PUPS ARE RESCUES, THEIR BREED MIX AND BIRTH DATES ARE UNKNOWN BUT WITH THE HELP OF OUR VET WE MAKE THE BEST EDUCATED GUESS. MOST OF THE PUPS ARE IN FOSTER CARE DOWN SOUTH WITH A RESCUE GROUP THAT WE HELP 

Currently in Kentucky

Sweet as a candy bar, this is Hally an 8 month old, purebred chocolate Labrador Retriever. She currently weighs 60# but will likely grow more and attain around a 70-80# weight. 

A high energy labby that has not had much of a life until coming into rescue, is much like a 2-year old toddler---VERY busy and into EVERYTHING! On a scale of 1-10 she is a 9.5!  

Hally LOVES WATER of any kind--ponds, streams, muddy puddles (as you can see in one of her photos) so a home life that includes access to water (or snow) on a regular basis is a plus.  She is a very sweet girl and loves to give kisses.  

THIS DOG IS IN KENTUCKY and will require:

* Home with a physically fenced yard
*Need a home more rural in nature, no apartments/condo/small house or city environment
*Needs strenuous daily exercise morning/noon/night to burn off energy. 
*A home with children over the age of 12
*Needs  at least an hour run/walk both am and pm and play time in the yard.  
*She would benefit from doggy daycare but NO DOG PARKS 
*Someone who has time to do obedience, she is a jumper and needs leash work 
*Someone who is home more often than not
*Hally is a very sweet girl and is a true submissive so she will need a home with a dog that isn't too dominant and intimidating or to be an only dog.
*No cats!

On a scale of 1-10 she is a 9.5!  

A dog like this will require her people to be home more often that not with a 4 hour limit on time alone at the least for the next year.  If your pre/post covid life doesn't allow for that, then this isn't the dog for you.  If you are excited to have an exercise/outdoor activities companion that loves you unconditionally, then HALLY IS THE DOG FOR YOU!!!  

GHR ONLY ADOPTS TO ADULTS OVER THE AGE OF 25 AND PUPPIES TO  PEOPLE WHO HAVE TIME FOR THEM. WE DO NOT ADOPT TO FAMILIES WITH CHILDREN UNDER THE AGE OF 5.
 
It doesn't matter where the pups are from; it only matters where they live the rest of their lives. If you are interested in adopting, please complete an application at www.goldenhuggs.org, this is the first step in the process. The adoption fee is $585 which includes spay or neuter, shots  age appropriate and transportation to the New England drop off points. For more information, please contact  info@goldenhuggs.org.

animal.description:
Loving, playful & affectionate, everyone meet our #Queen #WiggleButt Ms. #Nala. She's 4 years old, 55lbs, and an American Staffordshire Terrier mix. At the end of the day, Nala is honestly just the biggest lover that you'll ever meet. Nala craves human companionship, loves her daily walks, enjoys sunbathing in the backyard, lives for belly rubs, she's all about cuddles & movie nights & loves to give big kisses. She's 100% potty trained, 100% crate trained and does well on a leash.  Nala knows all of her basic commands and is very eager to please. The perfect family for Nala would be one that is active, loves the outdoors, an avid runner or someone who loves going on daily walks, and definitely a family that loves cuddles & puppy kisses.

When it comes to people, Nala loves everyone she meets! She loves & adores children and would make the perfect family pet. She'd do best in a home with kids over 10 years of age because at times she doesn't always understand her strength. Nala would thrive best as the only dog in her furever home, although she has made a few friends while in our care. Nala does not do well with female dogs,  but does well with submissive male dogs with a proper introduction. But once again, we would like her to be the only dog in her forever home. Nala absolutely adores the cat that is currently in her foster home- especially when it comes to cuddle time.

Adoption Requirements: No Exceptions
- Fenced in Yard Required
- Needs to be the ONLY DOG in her new home
- Nala would thrive best as the only dog in the home, but does do well with most submissive male dogs & does great with the male cat in her current foster home

Want To See More Pics:
https://www.petfinder.com/dog/nala-50060051/mi/ferndale/pro-pet-otic-foundation-mi1050/

Nala is currently up for adoption through Lending A Helping Paw Dog Rescue located in Metro Detroit. Her adoption fee is $150  & will include her distemper, rabies, bordetella, parvo, & lepto vaccines; deworming; microchip; heartworm test; fecal test & being fixed. Nala is currently on both flea & tick prevention and has had her ProHeart 6 Injection for heartworm prevention. 

***PLEASE READ THIS ENTIRE POST & FOLLOW THE INSTRUCTIONS****

Lending A Helping Paw Dog Rescue; previously known as the PRO-PET-OTIC Foundation, is a 100% Foster-Based Rescue that is ran by all Volunteers. Which means that we are not a shelter & each animal is in an actual home with a foster family. We kindly ask that you put any questions within the email & our team of Volunteers will get back to you. With the overwhelming amount of emails please be patient with our 100% volunteer family and we will get back to you. The application MUST BE filled out, a Vet Check MUST BE completed by our team, as well as a phone interview before we do a 'Meet N Greet.'
 
How To Apply:
If you're interested in adopting one of our available dogs:
1. Email LendingaHelpingPaw313@gmail.com with the dogs name as the subject when you ask for the adoption application.
2. Once you have completed the application, please print it out, fill it out, scan it, & then email it back to LendingAHelpingPaw313@gmail.com. If you do not have a scanner, please take a picture with your phone and we kindly ask that you sent all attachments into one email.
3. Please make sure to call your vet to grant our organization permission to do a vet check on your current pet.
4. If you are interested in more than one dog, please list your top 3 choices on the completed application.
5. Please be honest & truthful on your application. We always do a vet Check. We always do a home visit. And we always have both the prospective families & dogs best interest at heart!

Thank you in advance for all of your love & support,
The Lending A Helping Paw Dog Rescue Family

Bella would not do well in a home with lots of people coming and going, and she would be best with no other animals. Bella is truly a diamond in the rough. Bell is now fully vetted, vaccinated, spayed and chipped. Our vet felt Bella has had at least one litter of puppies. We are looking for a home that won't dump this girl ever again and give her the love she deserves. Bella has had some formal training as she knows sit, stay, down and more. Bella will need an experienced Doberman owner and fenced yard. Bella is now fully vetted, but we had learned prior to coming to UDR, not one of the three past homes were responsible enough to see that Bella received any kind of vet care when they temporarily owned her. Sadly was passed from home to home "Free" on Craigslist. Our vet felt Bella possibly has already had a litter of puppies in her past. Bella does tend to bond quickly to one person and she will for sure be very loyal to that one person who she can trust. Bella is truly a diamond in the rough.  Initially fearful of new things we have been working with her and feel she is ready for a foster or adoptive home to continue where we started with her. Please apply to foster or adopt if you have a fenced yard, no other pets and a home without a lot of activity.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Meet Gomez! Watch him cutely prance with his prize bone as he searches for its perfect hiding place. https://youtu.be/jnSdymVIoMk

Gomez is a true romantic, affectionate, and has a healthy appetite for life. Born around June 2017, his ideal weight is around 100 pounds of gorgeous fluffiness.

Gomez (as in the Addams family) was found as a super-skinny stray. He quickly showed his big, happy smile. He doesn't jump on people, and is well-mannered in the house. He is pretty mellow for the most part. He can be a little goofy sometimes, but usually displays his mature side.

He is so cuddly! He loves getting attention and lots of petting. He adores interacting with his people. He is good with kids. He is happy to meet and be hugged by every single child he meets.

He is enjoying learning how to play with other dogs, and he has been having fun playing with his new furry friends in his foster home. He gets along nicely with all of them - male, female, large, medium, small. They are teaching him that toys are fun!

He could be happy in a forever home with other dogs that he likes. He could also be happy as an only dog in the right home.

He loves to run! He hopes for a family that will keep him engaged in their lives and understands that he is sometimes lazy, and sometimes gets bursts of energy.

He needs a sturdy six-foot fence. Sometimes he gets excited about something he hears or sees on the other side, and he digs to get out. A wooden fence might be best, but it definitely needs to be 6' with a latch he can't open.

He is an avid barker! He warns you of possible intruders for days after they have gone - even if the interloper was just a dog he didn't want to be there! He will continually remind folks working next door that there is no trespassing on his property.

Gomez is house trained, crate trained, and rides nicely in a car. He walks really well on-leash. He is not much of a barker, only warning sometimes at things he can see on the other side of the fence.

Gomez should not be placed in a home with cats.

SPIN Pyrs are all in foster homes in the Dallas/Fort Worth area. Potential adopters are asked to make travel arrangements if they live elsewhere. All SPIN dogs are spayed or neutered, current on vaccinations and on heartworm prevention. Please go to our website www.SpinRescue.org and fill out an application for this great Great Pyrenees!

animal.description:
To adopt please fill out an adoption  http://www.happydogrescue.org/Application595.html

Sadie is a 3yo female Great Pyrenees/lab mix who was rescued as a stray in Memphis. Friendly, well-socialized, gentle. Sadie is recommended as an only dog. Typical of the breed, Sadie is choosy about her dog friends; she gets along with some dogs but not all dogs. Not recommended for cats because she likes to chase them. Recommended for children 12 years and older because little kids make her nervous. Medium-high energy level outside, quiet and well-mannered in the house.  Housebroken.  Learning basic commands.  Loves to be with her people.  Good on a leash, rides great in the car. Sadie has a limp and our vet says Sadie's rear L leg was injured in the past, probably hit by a car, broken in 2 places, never treated. But despite the limp, Sadie gets around very well as you can see from the video. Healthy and fully vetted, current on shots, spayed, weighs about 85 pounds.  AWESOME Pyr mix will make a wonderful companion for an active family who loves the breed.

Here's a note from Sadie's rescuer and foster mom:  My husband and I had this sweet girl wander into our yard early November. She has a distinct limp, was covered with fleas and ticks and was full of intestinal worms. We were unable to find her owner and believe she was intentionally dumped.  We took her to our vet and she has now been fully vetted.  She is heart-worm negative and is worm free and no longer has fleas or ticks.   The vet took x-rays of her back leg and she was obviously hit by a car at some point and broke her femur and tibia.  Unfortunately, this was allowed to heal without medical intervention. She now has a limp because one leg is shorter than the other.  Our vet has recommended that she be treated with joint supplements and physical therapy and that this would probably be a lifetime issue. We introduced her to our pack (three rescues), and one of our female dogs did not interact well with her.  She never seems to instigate any issues with other female dogs but will react and defend herself.  This broke our hearts because she's sooo sweet!  She is so wonderful, and we all just want the best for her. 

To adopt please fill out an adoption  http://www.happydogrescue.org/Application595.html 

Contact us at reply@happydogrescue.org

Visit us at  http://www.happydogrescue.org

Cyrus is a stunning 6 year old pure bred bi-color German Shepherd Dog. 
He loves to play fetch and loves to play and wrestle with his canine friends in his foster home. 
Cyrus is a Velcro dog. He needs to be with his family indoors or out. 
Cyrus has excellent house manners.  He is fully housebroken, crate trained when needed. He will chill around the house on a rainy day and not drive you crazy to want to play. He’s happy to play or to sit and chill indoors. 

Cyrus is good with adult cats that are not afraid of him. However, he will chase kittens. So we do not leave him unattended when we have foster kittens. 

Sadly Mr Cyrus has killed a goat he can no longer be trusted around livestock. 

Cyrus needs a home with an EXPERIENCED HANDLER. Someone that knows the breed and knows how to handle this amazingly intelligent dog.  

His one flaw is that he barks when he gets excited. I mean he barks a lot. Then his excitement will die down and he’ll stop and be the amazing dog we all know he is. 

Cyrus is neutered, microchipped, fully vaccinated and is heartworm negative.

Available now!
Adoption fee $350 plus tax
Fostered in Plano

Interested in adopting?? please go to our website and complete an adoption application today www.dfWGermanShepherdrescue.org

animal.description:
ADOPTION REQUIREMENTS
Fenced yard
Local to Springfield adoption only until after Daisy is spayed


Hi and thank you for coming to read about us.. We were found as stray and about to be parents when we were able to come to this nice rescue. We are looking for a new family that will love us both as we really love each other and can't be separated. This is what our foster mom says about us...

Dash and Daisy are DONE with being parents!?? They are ready to be empty nesters and never look back. They are bonded, eat together cuddle together and look for each other and whine if the other isn't around. They are both beagle mixes, roughly 25 lbs, and between 1 and 2 years old. Dash is house trained and Daisy is still working on it. She's had a lot going on taking care of the 5 babies. They love other dogs, cats and kids. We are still working on manners, so kids under 5 are probably not a good idea just because they might get knocked over. They are pretty high energy, and have the beagle bellow down pat. Due to these 2 reasons, they would not be a good fit in an apartment setting and require a 6 ft privacy fenced yard to burn some of that energy off. These two are absolutely precious and just want to love their people all of the time. They are incredibly special pups and whoever adopts them will be so lucky!

If you would like to meet Daisy and Dash send us an email to theloveofk9s@yahoo.com and we will get back to you a quick as we can.

Adoption donation pays for all vetting...both spay and neuter, heart worm tests, all vaccinations, deworming, flea prevention, microchips and wellness exams

animal.description:
To be considered for adopting a dog from Canine Lifeline, you must have an approved application must be on file. Please visit http://www.caninelifeline.org/adoption-process/ for more information about our adoption process and to submit an online application.

Luna is a beautiful 2.5 year-old Black Lab mix spayed female who lost her home along with another dog when her family was having a baby and no longer wanted the dogs. We can only imagine how confusing it must have been for Luna to have lost her home but she is making the best of it and looking forward to starting over in a true forever home. Luna is very friendly with people but we have found that she can be particular about her dog friends so does need to be the only dog in the home. Luna has had excellent crate manners in her foster home and is very likely to be housetrained although we can't guarantee that she won't have a few accidents in her new home as she gets used to the new routine. She will sit on command for a treat and likely knows more commands that we haven't discovered yet. Luna can also catch treats on the fly like a pro. She can be reactive with other dogs when walking on a leash so would do best in home in a quiet neighborhood or rural area where she'll have a yard with a secure aboveground fence. Luna does have a high prey drive and will also try to chase squirrels and other small critters when on a walk. We wouldn't be comfortable placing her in a home with cats. Luna loves her squeaky ball and looks forward to a new home where she can safely run and play to her heart's content. Luna weighs about 60 pounds and her adoption fee is $325. She's spayed, heartworm negative and on monthly preventative, up to date on vaccinations including bivalent canine influenza, wormed, on flea and tick preventative, and microchipped. As part of the adoption process, all adopters must commit to a two-week adjustment period to make sure it's a great match before the adoption is finalized. Please email info@caninelifeline.org if you're interested in Luna. An approved application is required before we schedule meets with any of our dogs. Please note that we don't place our dogs in homes with children under 7 years of age. We correspond via email so please check your junkmail or spam folder to make sure our reply hasn't landed in there. Please visit our website at www.caninelifeline.org to see more photos of Luna and to submit an online application if you live in Northeast OH.

The Baldwin County Animal Shelter is often operating at capacity, this means that for every dog or cat that comes in, another must leave via rescue or adoption, or risk being euthanized for space.  Multiple dogs and cats come to the shelter EVERY DAY, which means animals must also be moving out at the same rate. Unfortunately, sometimes there are larger adult, "pitbull" or mix-breed dogs that are continually overlooked for their younger or more "adoptable" counterparts. Please consider adopting a new best friend today!

***Thank you for your interest in Magnificent Mutts and Meows. We hope everyone is saying safe during this challenging time. Due to the current regulations set forth by Governor Pritzker on group gatherings we will not be having adoption events until further notice. As an all foster based rescue this means that all meets will be by appointment only. Your whole family must be available to attend the meet as there will be no second meets scheduled to help limit contact between our team and the public. To help streamline the process please make sure your current pets are up to date, you have landlord/HOA approval, and that you are prepared to take the dog home with you immediately before submitting an application. Thank you & Please stay safe!***

Ranger just arrived! Turned into a local animal shelter when his owners said they did not have time for him. It was clearly obvious to the shelter that he had had zero training in his young life. Approx 2 years old and 70lbs Ranger does need a strong handler. GSD or working dog experience needed. As with any dog up for adoption we recommend obedience training to make Ranger be the best boy he can be! We know at this time he does need a fenced in yard so - no apartments/townhomes/condos for this hunk, and any children in the home should be 10+ due to his mouthiness and exuberance! We do also know no cats, or small dogs for Ranger. He would do best as an only dog.

More information and additional restrictions may be added once he fully settles into foster care and we learn his full likes and dislikes.

If you are interested in adoption, please complete the Application to Adopt which you can find on our website (
www.magnificentmutts.org
) No phone calls please. Emails only.

Adoption Donation $300 (cash only)

Please visit www.magnificentmutts.org for the online dog or cat application.

Adoption Fees*

Adult cats starting at $125, Kittens starting at $165.
Dogs/Puppies starting at $225 minimum
Prices subject to change, please contact for specific adoption donations.

animal.description:
WANTED: A special foster home for a boxer girl in need. Could it be you or someone you know?

Delilah is a 2 year old boxer female that has been diagnosed with Ulcerative Colitis. She needs a home where she can recover and we can get her condition under control so that she can eventually be adopted. She has already made improvement under vet care. She still poops 8 or more times a day but in almost all cases will tell her human she needs to go outside. She has only had a few accidents in the home and no longer needs diapers. Due to her condition she is a bit underweight at 36 pounds.

Other than the ulcerative colitis, Delilah is an amazing dog. She is exceptionally good with both adults and kids, and gets along well with other dogs (we aren't sure about cats). She walks nicely on a leash, and is otherwise housebroken, but she is not yet crate trained. Delilah bonds with her human and wants to be with them as much as possible, she even refuses to dine alone and will need company while she eats.

WCBR is looking for a foster that can commit to Delilah's care. This includes taking her to all needed vet appointments, administering medications, following a strict diet 3x per day, and willing to log changes and improvement in her care. Fortunately, we have an amazing volunteer with experience with this condition in dogs that will be available for questions and advice as needed. Someone that is home often and will not leave Delilah alone for more than a few hours is key.

WCBR will cover the costs of her food, veterinary expenses, and any special supplies needed for her care.

If you may be able to provide the foster home Delilah needs, please submit a WCBR Foster Application via our website, www.westcoastboxer.rescue.org/adpot, and also email angela@westcoastboxerrescue.org to let us know about your interest. Feel free to share this post with dog-loving friends who might be able to foster Delilah.

Helps us get Delilah home! WCBR and Delilah appreciate your assistance!

** Please note: West Coast Boxer Rescue does not adopt female dogs to homes that already have a female dog.

Get to know us:

https://www.westcoastboxerrescue.org

https://www.facebook.com/WestCoastBoxerRescue

Twitter: @wcboxerrescue

Please follow us on our Facebook page: http://www.facebook.com/WestCoastBoxerRescue.

animal.description:
Hi there! I'm Spot-a-kiss. Yep, I have a unique name.  I wonder if you smiled when you said it in your head -- I bet you did! Well, get ready for that to be a normal part of our life together. You smiling. Me smiling. We are bound to have very sore cheeks I think! 

I'm full of joy and love. It's a safe bet that we will hit it off right from the start! I meet people in a friendly way because I'm a confident boy. I enjoy affection, being close to you, and making you proud.  I'm one of those sorts of dogs that gets along well with everyone. I hope you like to give belly rubs because I love to get them!

 I "sit" very nicely for treats when asked and I know "off". I will get into my bed when it's time to go to sleep, or you're welcome to have me sleep with you if you like. I also take the treat gently out of your hand too. I even am learning to "shake". I have a lot of decent manners already so you'll have an easy time training me (hint, keep yummies in your pocket).

I'm independent too: I like chewing on a Kong filled with treats, a rubber "stick" and cuddling on the couch. Once I get comfy in my surroundings I will have more and more fun playing with toys. I really, really, really want to find a family of my very own. I'm so excited about the possibilities! Have you pictured me in your home with you? You have? Awesome! Let's meet soon and make some plans together. Love, Spot-a-kiss

animal.description:
Senior Hearts Rescue and Renewal is the only licensed senior dog rescue organization in Western Pennsylvania. We do not have a shelter or a public facility. ALL of our dogs reside in foster homes in the greater Pittsburgh, PA area. 

We are a 100% volunteer organization. Please respect our volunteers' time. If a dog is listed on PetFinder, he/she IS available for adoption. We cannot reply to messages, phone calls, and emails about a dog until we have received, reviewed, and approved an adoption application. 

Our ADOPTION application is found at www.seniorhearts.org Completing this application is the first step in our adoption screening process. You MUST complete the application in entirety in order to be considered as a potential adopter.  Please select "More About Us" for further details on our adoption requirements.  You can meet a dog ONLY after we have completed our adoption approval process.

If you are looking at the dog below, it most certainly means the dog is available for adoption. We look forward to receiving your application in hopes that you are able to meet our adoption requirements and provide this dog a loving furever home.

And now a little message from Jazz herself...

I’m ready to find my furever home. I’m 13yrs young and weigh 18lbs. I’m looking for a calm home with a fenced yard. I like to be outside, even in the snow. I also need long walks. They help me stay young! 

I’m a quiet girl who would make an excellent home office companion. I promise to sleep at your feet for those endless hours of zoom meetings. 

I’m hoping to find a home that has another dog. I really do enjoy the companionship of a dog sibling. I don’t mind sharing my home with cats either. I’m just an all around good girl. 

I can be adopted within a two-hour radius of Pittsburgh, PA. If you want to meet me you must first complete the adoption application at www.seniorhearts.org

Cooper is 8 months and weighs 30lbs,

(BARK)might have the perfect match for you.

(BARK) is having a difficult time trying to get Cooper adopted, that is because the 8 month old pup is deaf.

Cooper can adapt very well, he knows what's going on. He can't hear you. But can respond to the tug of his leash,  he's very mindful of his surroundings and what's going on, so it's just a matter of that he can't hear.

Cooper enjoys car rides and tummy rubs Cooper can’t live with small kids, only homes with kids who are 10 years old or older, because he can’t hear them coming and he might get startled.

You have to be willing to take the time to work with him,he would probably be great if he learned a little sign language it's different than having a regular dog because you call them back, so you have to be mindful of that. 

He can't hear you, so a little bit of training for him would be perfect and would just do best in a home with someone who is willing to give him that time and attention.

animal.description:
DEAF DOGS ARE THE BEST, and Bleu is NO EXCEPTION!

Bleu's hobbies include frolicking and splashing in creek beds, problem solving how to climb up and down rocks, being your best friend and living life to the fullest. He really has a way of wanting everyone around him smile and enjoy life from his point of view without being imposing.

He's active, athletic, engaging and genuinely happy. You find yourself smiling along with him every step of the way.

Bleu is an adventure fiend, and would love to have a doggy companion who wants to romp and play with him. He could coexist great in a home with small and large dogs that are READY TO RUMMMBBBLLLE but also know how to just chill and hang out sometimes. He would prefer not to live with cats.

As a deaf dog, he's very well adjusted and trusting of his handler. He bonds quickly and loves completely. He is everything a two-year-old boy should be, full of life. He will benefit from a home and family dedicated to his continued success and he will thrive as he continues to learn more as he so smart and engaged with his humans. 

All dog adoptions include the following:
--Spay/neuter surgery
--All current vaccinations
--Microchip with free chip registration
--Free wellness exam through VCA Animal Hospitals
--Access to our Behavior Helpline for the lifetime of the pet
 
For more information or to schedule an appointment to meet this pet, please complete a Dog Adoption Questionnaire online. You can also email us at adoptions@lostourhome.org.

Looks like: Terrier Mix
Male, 10 years old, 15 pounds

This fella is a love bug. He adores people, and was previously best buds with a cat! They used to play together! He enjoys playing with kiddos as well. Snix is peachy around other dogs, too. 

Snix has a lot to say when he is excited. He does tend to be barky, especially in the car. We think he might learn to stop that with someone patient who can help with his training. We have not seen him barking while alone; it is a reaction to him being overly excited. 

Snix was diagnosed with oral melanoma in November 2020. He had the melanoma removed and went through two months of cancer treatment with Dr. Arteaga at Animal Cancer Center. He is now done with his treatment and is cancer free! 

Our hope is that he goes on to live a regular life span. He is looking for an adopter who is willing to give him all the love he deserves for the rest of his life knowing that he is a cancer survivor. 

Snix came to us because his senior guardian moved to assisted living facility.

Curtis is 5-6 years old, 37 lbs. He is super sweet.
Curtis is a sweet boy who is very human and dog friendly.  He is also great with kids!

He is crate trained and will often go to his crate to relax without being asked.  He is still working on house training and only has the occasional accident.   

He walks great on leash and is not reactive to other dogs.  

Curtis is very accommodating.  He will walk at a steady pace if you like to power walk, but he will also slow down and patiently wait if he’s walking with a slower senior dog who likes to sniff a lot.  He is very calm in the house, but will also get energized and frisky at playtime.  He lives in foster with a larger senior male and they get along very well. 

Curtis is a little shy at first, and it took him a few weeks to come out of his shell.  But he now likes to run and chase balls and cuddle in your lap.  He will make a great addition to any home because he is very easy going and friendly!

animal.description:
Hey there, pitty lovers! Please let us introduce Diamond.  If this pretty girl could talk, she’d tell you that her past hasn’t shined very brightly.  She was rescued after being observed lying in a ditch for three days by passersby.  Finally, a kind couple stopped to pick her up and brought her home with them.  No one knows how she got in the ditch – or why she remained there.  She was terrified so it’s believed that someone pushed her out of a car.  Thankfully, she was not injured…just very scared.  She has since been well loved in the home of her rescuers while she waits for a place to hang her leash forever.  

Diamond is about 3 years old and weighs in at 71 pounds.  She’s an American Staffordshire Terrier with beautiful blue/black coloring.  She is an affectionate high energy girl who loves attention.  Her foster family adores her and would love to keep her, but they have two resident cats and Diamond thinks cats are for chasing or chomping on.   They are giving her very good care and a safe home, but she has to spend much of her time outside or kenneled and they want a better life for her.  Her strength and rambunctiousness would likely not be a good combination for a home with small dogs, but she gets along great with her foster family’s large dogs and loves to play with them.

This girl is truly a diamond in the rough with the potential to sparkle in a home with the experience and time to devote to her training.  Primarily an outside dog, she’s working on her house manners and does well inside as long as she’s taken out regularly.  Her leash skills are in need of work.  She is a strong girl and tends to pull.  Her foster mom says she’s a sweetheart who wants to please her people and, with patience and practice, she’ll get it down.  Her best home will be with adults only, or teens. Though she would not intentionally harm anyone, she can jump high when excited and could knock over young children.  A home with fenced yard would be ideal.

Diamond has been spayed, is up to date on vaccines and micro-chipped.  She’s also on monthly flea/tick and heartworm preventative.  If you are a bully breed lover and have the time and experience to give this girl her chance to shine and live the life she deserves, please contact Chris at rescue3@earthlink.net for an application and she’ll send one right out to you.  Her adoption fee is $300. She’s waiting for you!

Like us on Facebook at www.facebook.net/pawsclawsnewengland

Meet FRANCO! He's about 1.5yo and full of life! We rescued FRANCO from the Downey shelter where he had shown up with a broken leg. He spent a couple of months with a splint on and now he's ready for a forever home.

FRANCO is a young, athletic dog who responds well to a confident leader who has the time to help keep this "busy" dog engaged.  We think an adopter with a yard who is active and has experience with "training" would be ideal for Franco.  He is young and unlearning habits such as "jumping up" so we recommend a home with older children. 

With dogs, FRANCO is playful but has a rough and rowdy style and can get himself in trouble - just like with humans, he would do well with an older confident dog who can teach him some manners.

FRANCO is about 65lbs and currently at our kennel in South Gate. He is crate-trained, neutered, micro-chipped and current on vaccinations. If you are in the Los Angeles area and interested in meeting FRANCO, please fill out our brief online questionnaire (copy and paste link): www.downtowndogrescue.org/adoption-questionnaire

Please note that while we are closed to the public we will not be responding to pet inquiries. Once animals are posted, we immediately begin receiving adoption applications. With one volunteer available to review all applications, we appreciate your patience as you wait for an email response. Adoption appointments are scheduled first come with an approved application, first served. (See our adoption procedures below.)

Duey transferred to us from another shelter where he was surrendered by his owner who had originally adopted him. Duey is a gentle giant with a lot of sweet and happy to share. While he has a quite charming personality and demeanor, Duey would do best in a home without small children as their grabbing, crawling and unexpected noises may make him nervous. His ideal home would include adults and children over 12 years of age, a tall wooden fence for safe exercise, and the ability to handle him on a leash--he is a very large boy. Duey is more than ready to find his forever home. Duey's estimated DOB is 11/16/2014. He weighs about 116 pounds. Duey is house/leash trained and seems to understand several commands including sit and stay.

HSPC's adoption fee is seventy-five-dollars through December 31, 2020, unless stated otherwise within the pet's description. At times, our adoption fees are lowered during special events that are posted to our website or Facebook page. Every pet that is available for adoption has been spayed/neutered, microchipped, and is up-to-date on vaccinations including heartworm preventative (canines). Adopters are required to schedule a wellness exam with their veterinarian at their cost within 7 days of adoption.

Please only submit one application. Once you are contacted by email, you will have an opportunity to provide us with any additional animal(s) under consideration.

animal.description:
PLEASE COMPLETELY READ THE ENTIRE DESCRIPTION 

We are a foster home based rescue organization. **Only approved adopters can meet our dogs** 

If you are interested in adopting please follow these instructions before contacting Rescue4All. Virtually all of your questions will be answered by following these instructions: 

1. Go to our website www.rescue4all.org 
2. Thoroughly read through the HOW TO ADOPT tab
3. Thoroughly read through the OUR PROCESS tab
4. then fill out an online application from your laptop or desktop computer or click on the mobile friendly link on the application page.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Pancho is a large mixed breed male, not sure how old he is.

Pancho was a neglected street dog in Guadalajara...no name...no family...and was in extremely bad shape.

He just happened to collapse in front of the right house to find the perfect person, Melissa who is a rescue dog advocate, a Rescue4All supporter, and the manager of The Urban Canine North. She was down there visiting family. 

After a lengthy recovery, he was flown from Mexico to Spokane thanks to our amazing supporters at Urban Canine!

He has lived a life of survival on the streets which, not surprisingly, has left him with some issues with other animals. 

We got him tested for heartworm & tick born illnesses which was all negative.

He had to have part of his left ear amputated because of the necrotic tissue.

He has been neutered, vaccinated, dewormed, and microchipped.

He has some significant muscle atrophy on the left side of his face that we are trying to figure out the reason for, but the wounds on the side of his head and his ear have finally healed.

What we know about Pancho is that he is amazing with humans, he loves attention and just being with you. He loves soft beds and being warm. He is great on a leash and just wants to be safe.

animal.description:
Zeus- 12 year old neutered male Labrador Retriever mix, 70 pounds, house trained, not good with dogs, not good with cats, good with kids, very friendly, affectionate, very smart, loves to play, very sweet.

Seeing any dog in a shelter is sad, but seeing a senior in the shelter is heartbreaking. Zeus was surrendered when his person lost their job and could no longer afford to properly care for him. He is now looking for a new family to love and care for him as he deserves to be. Zeus is a big boy and quite peppy for his age. He will chase a ball with the cutest old man run. He loves to take walks. This boy loves people and is so friendly with everyone. Zeus is missing some hair and appears to have some allergies that his new family would need to be wiling and able to deal with that. We are told he isn't good with other animals but he's awesome with kids of all ages. He comes to you house trained and having lots of experience living in a home. Adopting a senior is so rewarding and easier than adopting a younger dog. They require little exercise but do expect the same amount of love. Senior pets are often overlooked in a shelter and so are black dogs so Zeus has two strikes against him. He needs a hero to step up and show this old guy that he still matters. You can meet Zeus by calling 757-385-4444 or clicking on this link to make an appointment https://www.facebook.com/VBAnimalCareandAdoptionCenter The shelter is located at 341 S Birdneck Rd, Virginia Beach, VA.
