animal.description:
Milo is a 2 year old Pug Chihuahua mix who is active, cuddly, and full of personality. Milo loves to play fetch with furry squeaky toys, and be outside. Milo was left outside a lot with his littermates, and is afraid of people now. He is wary of every new person he meets, and it takes time for him to warm up but once he does, he is a sweet, smart and loving pup! 

Milo had no training prior to coming to our rescue so he is still learning to walk on a leash, and is working on learning commands. Milo is house trained but will need to be watched for marking when he first moves into his new home. 

Milo is a slow to warm up guy who
needs an adopter with experience. He can be growly if cornered when he doesn’t know you. He only takes a day or two to fall in love with his people and is worth the wait. He doesn’t have much experience with the world so is easy frightened on walks, will sit down and refuse to move at times. If approached by strangers when on a leash he will try to get out of his harness and run. When scared he barks and growls. 

Milo is growly and scared with kids. He uses his mouth when he is excited and can nip or mouth you to get your attention. We solve this by giving him a small furry toy to hold to keep his mouth busy. Milo would do best in am adults only home or one with patient teenagers. 

He likes to think he is the head of any pack he is a part of so will do best with submissive other dogs. He would be happy to be an only dog as well. He chases and plays too roughly with cats though he doesn’t intend to harm them. 

Milo is crate trained, comes when he is called, and is a pretty independent guy. He is pushy with his love, climbing right on top of you and pushing everything and everyone else out of his way. We expect he will learn to be a little more polite with consistent training. Milo would love an active family who will patiently share the big world with him. He is great in a car!

We prefer an adopter who will meet him in person prior to adoption in our Columbia, TN rescue home. 

All dogs adopted are spayed/neutered, vaccinated including Rabies if over 14 weeks, microchipped, fecal tested, heart-worm tested if over 7 mo at arrival, flea/heartworm/tick preventative given monthly. Dogs are in foster homes in various locations but we are located in Columbia, TN. All dogs can be transported for free to adopters in the US and Canada. For faster reply, send us an email at arrowdogrescue@gmail.com

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.
THIS IS A COURTESY LISTING FOR "SHELLY". FOSTER OR ADOPTER NEEDED.

My friends call me "Shelly". I am a captivating, intelligent, and affectionate 4-year old, 55 lb. girl if I do say so myself.

I am house trained, know some basic commands, and am getting better on a leash. I eat way too fast- it appears that I had a pretty rough start in life- so I eat from a puzzle bowl to slow me down.

I am probably better off as an only pet, as I want all of the affection I was deprived of early on, but I would be open to meeting another male dog my size.

A home with older children or adults-only would be ideal for me, as I can be excited when I am happy. After all, I probably didn't have much to be excited about before.

Shelly is currently being fostered in Staten Island, NY. To learn more, please contact AmsterDog at info@amsterdog.org or fill out our application at www.amsterdog.org/application to get the process started.

animal.description: Howdy, My name is Piepie but you can call me pie. Paw named me that on account of something Popeye used to say, "That's all I can stands. I can't stands no more!" animal.description:
Gerald came to our veterinarian's clinic as a stray. He unfortunately had heartworms. He is now heartworm free, neutered, and up to date on vaccines. He loves people and gets along with other dogs but DOES NOT like cats. He needs a family to go on long walks with and to cuddle with at night. 

Application: www.maxshope.com

Adoption fee: $85

Please include your veterinarian name, number and the name your current pets are listed under. Also please check your information carefully. All current pets must be up to date on vaccines and spayed/neutered. Dogs must be on heart worm preventative.
Adoption Process: This is not a first come, first serve organization. We will process applications within 48 business hours of receiving them. The application must be completed in full including first and last name, complete address including city and state, complete veterinarian information(this will be checked and all pets must be neutered or spayed, up to date on all vaccines, and dogs must be current on heartworm prevention) and the name of all current pets in the household. We are 100% volunteers and I will not subject anyone who is giving of themselves and their time to hostile conversations. Please be patient with us. We are not paid for our endless hours and are looking for the BEST home for the babies in our care.

We will process your information and an email will be sent to the email you provide on the application within 48 hours.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Hi!! I'm Penny Jo, but some of my friends call me PJ.

I'm a happy, silly girl that just wants love and attention from my person. I LOVE toys, balls, ropes, and bones. Stuffed toys are my favorite because they are SO much fun to de-stuff!

When I'm not playing with my toys, I like to take a good cozy nap. I really like to cuddle up next to my foster mom so she can pet me. I love to go for walks and play outside, but I sometimes pull on my leash a little too hard when I'm excited so that is something I will need to continue to work on.

I know basic commands like sit and down and I know how to shake and ask (bark). Sometimes I get so excited about the treat you are going to give me or the toy you're going to throw that I start to ask (bark) for it before you tell me to.

I sleep in a kennel during the day and I am potty trained. I don't always love going into the kennel, but as long as you give me a treat I'll go right in. I like to go for rides in the car too. I like to sit in the back seat so I can look out the windows, but if there is no one in the passenger seat I like to come up front when you stop and go back to the back once you start moving again.

I am particular on my doggie friends and I need slow introductions to new dogs I meet. I like playing with my foster sister, but on my terms. She is a puppy and likes to annoy me all the time wanting to play, but I ignore her and then when she is calm and laying down I approach her to play for a few minutes.

From Penny Jo's foster mom:

Penny Jo cannot be around other animals when there is food is present (human or dog food). PJ is great on her own with food, but she will steal it if you leave it unattended. She will need to eat her meals in her crate or in her own space.

Penny Jo is an awesome dog that wants to please her person. She takes correction very well and is very smart and would love to learn more tricks to make her person happy.

Date of birth (estimated): 6/9/18

Good with Dogs: Slow introductions required - dog selective

Good with Cats: No

House Trained: Yes

Adoption Fee: $250

If you are interested in meeting or adopting this animal, please read the following before submitting an adoption application on our website - fureverhomerescue.com.

Adoption fee includes spay/neuter, microchip, age appropriate vaccinations, 4Dx test (covers tick-borne diseases ( A naplasmosis , Lymes, E hrlichiosis) as well as heart worm) & de-worming. We ask that our dogs live indoors unless otherwise stated & agreed upon. Applicants must live in MN within a reasonable distance from the Twin Cities Metro Area. We do not adopt out of state.

animal.description:
Kerri has made some major progress in the last month! She now comes when asked and loves hanging out with her canine companions. She's quite mischievous and LOVES her soft toys. She is often seen carrying around a squeaky toy and proudly showing it for all to see. Kerri is food motivated and with the right person will come out of her shell with time and patience. She's becoming less fearful every day.
.
5/27/20: Well they must be related haha! Kerri has also discovered the benefits of dog beds this morning!
.
Kerri came in to a shelter partner as part of a litter of feral puppies. Three of these dogs were unable to be placed locally which is when we were contacted. She has had very limited human interaction and will need a confident, patient partner going forward.
.
With time and patience we have no doubt Kerri will make an amazing companion for the right home. She will need another confident dog in the home to help teach her the ropes.
.
She will not be placed with kids or in an urban environment. She has been exposed to cats with no issues. We will post more information as we get to know her, so be sure to check back! 

PLEASE READ our procedures for adoption prior to making inquiry regarding this dog. If you are looking for additional photos, video, or information on this dog, you will likely find that by searching our facebook page for their photo/description album.
.
Please see our main website at www.mabcr.org for more information regarding the adoption of this or any dog from our rescue. 
.
Please note that while this dog is currently available, any dog on our site may have an adoption pending and may not be available to you at this time. The same dog may later become available if the adoption falls through. 
.
Our website www.mabcr.org will give you details on our adoption procedures as well as an application for adoption. An application must be submitted prior to 'matching' an adopter with a dog as all dogs do not fit into all homes. We pride ourselves in our adoption process, we take the time to get to know our adopters so that we can place a dog with them that they can enjoy for years to come.
.
Please understand that we will not discuss dogs with individual adopters until after the application process is completed.
.
Our rescue does not have a public facility, therefore there are no visiting hours. Appointments to visit with the available dogs are made after the application process has been completed by our staff.  
.
To assist any dog within the MABCR organization, please consider making a donation to the general fund or to the medical fund. All dogs coming into our rescue are fully vetted (s/n and core vaccines) prior to adoption.
.
Rescuing animals is quite expensive. If you are unable to adopt, but would like to help this, or any other animal in our system, please consider a sponsorship donation. 
For information on our sponsorship program, please contact Sarah at SLR@mabcr.org. 
.
Thank you for your interest in Mid-Atlantic Border Collie Rescue.

Mickey is continuing to learn about training, socialization, and partnership. So far Mickey has made great progress with his resource guarding and now prefers to play fetch instead of keep away. Mickey is soooo smart and picks up new cues in a flash. Mickey has been exposed to agility equipment and seems to love the sport. Hello, my name is SImba.  I was one of 9 puppies born after our mommy was pulled from a very high kill shelter in Houston, TX (on the day she was to be put to sleep, as she was very pregnant with us, and they had no place for her).  I was born 10/7/2016.  My siblings and I have been trying to find homes in Houston since we were little, but it is very hard to find people there that want to take care of us the right way.  We sat at hundreds of events, and people would say how cute we were, but we never found our places.  That is when the rescue started placing others in the Seattle area.  I just arrived here a short time ago.  I have one brother and two sisters that have found their homes, so I decided it is my turn to give it a go.  I am a tad shy.  I am really really sweet and loving, I just need time to get to know you and trust you.  Our mommy was of a nervous temperament, and I think we naturally are that from her.  My 3 siblings that went with their families recently, both have both required patience and loving support.  I hear they are doing great now, but they growled and were very timid the 1st few days… I’m sure I will be the same way.  We have had a lot of changes lately.  Once you give me a chance though, and I trust you as I do my foster family… I become a real ham.  I love to play.  I love to sleep with you.  I love to hang out and do whatever you are doing.  I do fairly well with going potty where I should as long as you keep me on a bit of a schedule.  I know how to use potty pads or go outside.  I am fairly small, so we little ones can only hold it so long though.  I probably won’t ever be great with small children, as they are not too familiar to me, except a few bad experiences at adoption events. I do ok with other doggies as long as they are not too intimidating, but I probably won’t ever flourish at daycare or dog parks.  I am happier just being around my person/ people.  I don’t mind kitties… my foster family has a few… some like to play, some do not… I have learned to stay away from kitties that tell me they do not want to play, and I give them their space.  Well, that is all for now… time to go play.  Let my rescue people know if you’d like to meet me, and after you fill out an application to be an approved adopter, they will schedule a time for us to meet each other.  Oh, I am fully vetted and up to date on my healthcare too.  

Adoption fee:  $500

animal.description:
Meet Sammy! This little love bug is just
the sweetest girl you'll ever meet! She's an almost 6yo, 52 lb. terrier mix looking for a new home due the stress of a new baby in the home. Sammy is loving, loyal and will happily snuggle up with you in bed or on the couch with a smile on her face (check out her videos for proof). She enjoy naps and down time as an adult, but she still has a lot of energy. She loves to run around (especially when she has a case of the zoomies), is almost always down to play (any toy you get for her will never go to waste!), and loves a good long walk, hike or even a short jog! She loves checking out new places and does well in the car and on road trips. She has the cutest little satellite ear and wagging tail when you talk to her!

Sammy
has fantastic house manners and loves to show off her basic commands for a treat (sit, stay, up, lay down, etc.) Her favorite special treat is peanut butter and she loves a good back scratch. She also has a few funny quirks such as loving to roll around in the grass on a sunny day and loving getting towel dried after a walk in the rain or a bath (she hates getting wet, but loves getting dried off!)

She would make a great companion animal or family pet for a family with adults only.
Sammy
loves her people and would do best in a home with someone who is around a lot. She can get very excited/playful around other dogs, so she would do best in a home with adults and no other pets or another very calm, uninterested dog (no cats).

While Sammy is not a LOVEPAWS dog, we will be helping her owners find her the best home. Please fill out our online adoption application at
www.lovepawspg.org
then email Katherine at Katherine.Lovepaws@aol.com.

animal.description: Hi! My name is Amalia! I was rescued from Puerto Rico by Big Dog Ranch & Rescue. When I arrived, I was only days away from giving birth to my litter of puppies! I am really a very sweet girl but sometimes I may seem a little bit standoffish. I like to play with other dogs here on the ranch but can be selective at times as far as who I choose to spend my time with. I'm looking for an experienced dog owner who is looking for a new best friend. I would probably do best in a house with older children and I am not feline friendly. While I could easily adapt to apartment style living, I would love to have a yard or at least an outdoor space since sun-tanning and rolling around in the grass are my two favorite activities. I'd like to live a quiet life, filled with lots of days just snuggling on the couch, and don't feel like you need to take me lots of places to keep me entertained, I'm perfectly happy chilling at home. I would benefit from some further training, particularly leash training and some potty training, to help me be the absolute perfect pup!

animal.description:
Ginge is a big snuggly warm, cuddly Pittie package. Ginger is an American Staffordshire terrier that would likely be called a redhead if she were a person. She has a stunning reddish brindle coat and a sweet face that just wants to be smushed and smooched on a daily basis. Ginger is about a year or two old and weighs around 50 lbs. She wants nothing more than to be with people and would be about the best foot warmer and space heater you could find this winter and every one moving forward. Like most of her breed, she is not interested in personal space and would love to be as close as possible for snuggle time, or just about any time. Ginger LOVES kids to be her play and snuggle buddies. She is young and active and would love regular walks. With a goal of making you happy, she already knows "sit" and would easily learn whatever you wanted to teach and would prove a quick study who thoroughly enjoys treats and reinforcement - peanut butter is one of her favorites!
Ginger enjoys simple things, like a good chew, a good snooze, and a good snuggle. She has the cutest snore and can be hilariously stubborn, but more than anything, she is just a loving, low-maintenance pup.
Ginger has made a number of doggie friends at the farm, but would be just fine being a solo dog as she likes to be in charge of the doggie pack and in all honesty, is so wonderful in and of herself it is hard to imagine sharing adoration with anyone else. Don't just take our word for it, this pittie package is just perfectly precious and you must come meet her ASAP!

Please note we are working with limited staff/volunteers at this time. For full details of our current adoption appointment policy, please see https://savinggracenc.org/adoption-appointments-during-this-time/. Highlights:

We are working with a very limited staff/volunteer base

We do not have the people power to respond to emails/call about specific dogs

Our appointments are limited to 2 people at a time and for a maximum of 30 minutes.

Please arrive at your appointment ready to meet the dogs we have available. At this time, many dogs are in foster families or not yet posted on our website. Be flexible and ready to meet any number of wonderful dogs available onsite at the time of your appointment.

All puppies and dogs at Saving Grace are crate trained, have been spayed/neutered, are up to date on their vaccinations, are on heartworm preventative and have been microchipped. Their adoption fee is $375.00. Each has been carefully screened for disposition and temperament in order to provide your home with a safe companion that will enjoy life as your new family member.

Our Adoption Form can be completed online at our website at https://savinggracenc.org/how-to-adopt/ .

An Adoption Form is required before setting up an appointment to meet with a potential adoptee or a foster home.

Sending an Adoption Form does not commit you to an adoption, it simply provides us with background information on potential homes.

If you'd like to donate to help cover the cost of care for these wonderful dogs awaiting new homes, please visit the donate page on our website at https://savinggracenc.org/donate-now/ .

Saving Grace is a small, non-profit 501-C3 organization operated by volunteers only. Most of our animals come from rural animal control shelters where lack of space and resources limit their time and adoption possibilities. Thank you for choosing Saving Grace! We look forward to helping you find your new companion and family member.

animal.description:
Meet Cool Dude Steve! 

This guy has a look all his own and we couldn't love it more! Steve was picked up as a stray in a rural area and taken to Kern County Animal Services. This short stack was very shut down in the shelter environment so he joined the Marleys Mutts team! 

Steve is slowly coming around in foster care. He'd likely never lived inside a house based on his initial behavior when inside his fosters home. Now he is crate trained and doing very well with his house training skills. 

Steve doesn't trust quickly and if pushed too hard or if people try to handle him too fast and too much before he knows them he absolutely has the potential to bite. He has a stoic/serious personality that isn't for everyone. He can be stubborn especially in the beginning but if given the time to decompress and get to know a new person he's great with them and kind of a goofball. He's good with dogs and ignores cats. We would not recommend he live in a home with children as they move quickly and could easily startle him and cause unwanted behavior. He hates car rides but LOVES going for walks. 

Steve's foster mom has a lot of experience with unsure dogs so is being very selective about the home he goes to as we don't want Steve returned because he's more dog that a potential adopter can handle. He wouldn't be the right fit for a 1st time adopter. She will be taking her time reviewing each application to determine if a home is the right home for Steve. If you think you might be his perfect home apply today! If you are interested in adopting a Marley's Mutts please fill out an application at http://marleysmutts.org/adoptionprocess/

animal.description:
Meet Fancy, a 3-year-old English Bulldog/Staffordshire mix. Her story begins on the day that a team in Oklahoma saved her from the euthanasia list of a crowded shelter. They discovered she was pregnant.

Fancy gave birth very soon after. She had a small litter and only one puppy was born breathing. Rescuers knew that they needed to find a foster home for this precious family to be nursed back to health, so Fancy and baby made their way all the way to Nebraska and Muddy Paws. 

Now Fancy was sad after having a stillborn litter, and her puppy wasn't growing properly without littermates to keep her warm and help her grow strong and healthy. There were two sick puppies in rescue who had to be separated from their mother early as she wasn't able to feed them properly. Fancy took them under her wing and nursed them next to her own. She was an amazing mother and loved them all dearly. They were inseparable - playing and cuddling together every day. Once the pups were old and healthy enough to leave mom, Fancy got to meet each of their adopters before taking them home. She gave each one a kiss as if she approved and then walked them to their car. 

Now, with Fancy's role as a mother complete, she is waiting for her own perfect home!

Fancy is a very healthy girl, although the vet noticed that her body showed signs of having multiple litters in the past. Our best guess is that Fancy was an ex-breeder dog who either escaped this harsh life or was abandoned. We are happy to report that although Fancy was an amazing mother to her single daughter and adoptive children, her days of breeding are over! She continues to help foster puppies in need, but her body is finally allowed to rest. She provides only sociliazation, cuddles and love now!

Being an ex-breeder dog may explain some of her quirks. This little girl is a dragon! She has no idea what toys are, except she recognizes they are Important and Treasure. She will steal toys and bones from everyone and hide them away under couch cushions, blankets and dog beds for safe keeping. She wasn't potty-trained when she arrived, but now she is nearly 100% pottyign outside! She is the queen of the house and demands pets and love from every visitor.

Walks consist of her trying to greet every person and walk up every driveway we go my. She walks on a loose-leash and is always attuned to her human. She doesn't need much exercise - this lazy girl would prefer a nice stroll through the neighborhood and then a date night cuddled up next to you!

Fancy's ideal home would be with a family that was home a good amoutn of time. If there are other dogs in the home, they need to be able to put up with her quirks! Dog intros are required with this silly girl. 

The suggested adoption donation for Fancy is $350. We are a 501c3 organization which means that your donation may be TAX DEDUCTIBLE. Your donation goes toward the high cost of veterinary care for our animals in rescue, as well as providing supportive services to animals in homes.

Information about the adoption process: All adoptions require a completed ADOPTION APPLICATION. Once your application is approved, we will put you in touch with the dogs foster to see if you and the pet are a good match. If so, we will arrange a meeting for you and the pet. The adoptions for all of our animals will take place in the Omaha, NE area and must be done by the adoptive family in person. We do not ship or deliver.

Please Note: We are a RESCUE, which is different from a shelter. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. We always select the right applicant for each dog, based on the dogs needs. If you and the dog are not a good match, we will help you select another dog, or we will keep your approved application on file for 6 months.

To learn about Muddy Paws Second Chance Rescue or donate to our animals, please visit our website at MuddyPawsSecondChanceRescue.com or our Facebook Page.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Update : Eloise LOVES the snow and is having a great time playing . She was seen recently by an Allergy specialty vet and she has had an initial Cytopoint injection and is receiving soaking baths hoping we can break the cycle and reduce or eliminate the itching that has probably gone untreated for a long time....but while her skin may be a little rough , her personality is still sweet and sunny to everyone she meets !

Update : From her foster " everyday we see more of the real Eloise.....she is a true delight!

She loves going for walks and prances as she walks !

She enjoys meeting people and dogs. Absolutely LOVES car rides .

Squirrels and ducks/geese don't seem to be of interest to her and so far , she has not met any cats while in foster.

She is still dealing with some itchiness and is on antibiotics for the next few days . Kennel life can be hard on dogs so we are hoping with consistent diet and care this will end.

When a local shelter contacted us about a super sweet girl that needed help, we couldn't say no. Look at that face ? Who could resist that look ?

What we know is she is very affectionate , likes toys, , fine with dogs and was scared of the shelter cat she met .

We don't know what happened to her or why her people didn't look for her , but she will be in an ASR foster home tomorrow night.

The shelter treated her for skin and ear infections , poor girl , she clearly didn't have the best life before but that has not diminished her sweetness .

If you are not yet approved to adopt from All Shepherd Rescue, please fill out our online application at www.allshepherdrescue.com. Our adoption fee is $350.00.

animal.description:
The super handsome three year old German Shepherd “Zeus” is a dedicated and loyal fellow who will make his new owner a fantastic companion.   Z, as he is affectionately called, is eager to please, fast to respond to routine basic commands and has successfully completed basic obedience training.   This active fellow must have a job to put his skills to use, continue to be socialized and have an environment where he gets plenty of exercise and a challenging job.   

Z has had little socialization and we are working to expand his horizons.   As a result, he demonstrates some initial trust issues initially when meeting a new person if he is placed in any type of fenced or caged in area such as a kennel (barrier aggression.    And, he is fearful of basic environmental items such as a mailbox because of this lack of exposure.    However, Z is growing every day and overcomes this quickly once he spends time with and comes to trust his new human.    He isn’t a jumper or climber and is quite content to remain in a fenced in area.   

The successful adopter will be an experienced German Shepherd owner with a proven record of handling German Shepherds, someone who knows the breed and is willing to invest time winning Z’s trust and someone eager to dedicate the time required to hone this great fellow’s skills.    Although Z has spent his entire life indoors and has not been exposed to other dogs, we have introduced him off leash to other German Shepherds and small dogs and he gets along well with the five dogs to whom he has been introduced.   He is extremely well house trained and must continue to be a dog with indoor privileges to bond with his human family.

Please go on-line, complete an application.   Phone Godbey Creek Canine Rescue for more details or to schedule an appointment.   336.972.4511

animal.description:
Cutie patootie OLIVER was taken into rescue shortly before Christmas after being found by a Good Samaritan in TN, and not a day too soon. Found alongside the entrance ramp to an interstate,  Oliver was starving and could barely walk he was sooo weak. His angel says he had a look of just giving up on life. He is doing so well now in our care that Oliver is now part of a play group enjoying playing outside for short periods because of the bitter cold. 

Oliver is such a sweet boy who has come such a long way since initial rescue. He is eating quality food, gaining his healthy weight back, about 3 pounds so far, and is getting appropriate exercise. He has been neutered, had dentals at the same time to eliminate having to put him under anesthesia a second time, and has been microchipped. 

Oliver is a purebred Beagle boy estimated to be about 4 to 5 years old and presently weighing 24 pounds. What a great age for a Beagle to join your family! Still very able, active and playful, but has outgrown that truly hyper Beagle puppy stage of boundless energy. The Beagle breed is a long lived breed with good care. One of our personal Beagles is 17 years old. 

Please visit also our rescue Facebook page where we post updates, pictures, and videos of all of our dogs, including Oliver. Petfinder limits us on the number of pictures and videos we can post. Facebook does not.  There you will be able to follow Oliver’s progress. The only applications we will be accepting right now for Oliver are foster-to-adopt to give him a home environment in which to further heal and complete needed medical care. The foster-to-adopt family will then be the first in line to adopt Oliver. And, yes, all of our Beagles are very popular and end up with multiple adoption applications. So, if you are smitten with Oliver and would like to foster his sweet self through complete vetting with the priority for being his forever family, please email Diana and dmoore2003@bellsouth.net.

animal.description:
This hound has a pending adoption.  Wild World AKA Hero is a 1 1/2 year old red brindle male who raced at approximately 71 pounds.   He arrived on 12/4/2020.  More information to follow.

Meet Hero! (Racing name Wild World)  Hero recently came to PA  from Florida. He's 1.5 years old, friendly, and loves to chase squirrels. He's getting used to living in a house....staying away from the hot stove, no "counter surfing", and learning how to go up and down steps. He's very smart and a quick learner--already housebroken AND trained to do his business in a very specific area of the yard! He knows the command "lay down" from clicker training. Hero loves his furry squeaky toy, and getting hugged and kissed by his foster mom. He'd be a great apartment dog--very quiet--just one small bark so far! He’s not cat safe, so he’ll need a home without cats. He was enthusiastic and sweet when meeting the little girl next door. Later this month (Dec) he’ll get neutered and will be ready for his forever home.
His foster mom's favorite times with Hero so far were when he was laying "cockroach" in his bed, when he nibbled her fingers like a little kiss and every morning when he greets her with his teeth chattering in excitement. All signs of a happy greyhound.

animal.description:
Roxy is a happy & friendly Pit/Lab mix who is 10 years old and weighs 60 lbs.  Based on her age & appearance, you may think she's an old lady, but on the contrary, Roxy is anything but ... She absolutely adores people and being taken out for long walks.  She is a sweet, social, medium energy girl who loves car rides, knows basic commands, and has awesome leash manners.  A fenced yard isn't necessary for this curious & spry gal because she's not super active, but she does really enjoy exploring & romping around outside so if you've got a fenced yard, she will definitely make good use of it!  Her goal is to keep herself & her family busy with daily adventures and she still has plenty of pep in her step & lots of love to share!  Roxy is looking for a calm, adult only household where ideally someone is home frequently to spend time with her.  She doesn't have separation anxiety, but she does like to have human companionship while she chews her toys and takes her daily naps!  Roxy is housebroken, crate trained, spayed, fully vaccinated & microchipped.  

For more information about Roxy, please email us at info@barkvilledogrescue.org. If you would like to adopt this sweet girl, please submit an application for her at https://www.barkvilledogrescue.org/applications

animal.description:
Meet Kerfuffle (or fuffle for short). 

He is an 8 months old (or younger), male, poodle mix. He is small, at only 5lbs, and is very likely done growing. He can be shy and a little bit snippy when approached too quickly. Because of this, he will not be approved for a home with children under 12. He does well with other dogs and cats and sleeps quietly in his kennel at night. We are working on his house training but he still needs more practice. 

When he came to us, he was starved and dehydrated to the point that he could not lift his head or open his eyes.  We were really surprised that he survived. For this reason, we will be very particular about the home he goes to. We must warn you that Fuffle is a crotchety young boy. He is not the dog that’s going to go running up to a new person and want their attention. He will back away while growling and/or barking and; if you go to get him when he does not want to be picked up, he will bite you.  

At the time of adoption, he will be fully vaccinated, neutered and microchipped before going to his new home. He is heartworm negative and has been started on preventatives.  A vet reference and home visit are BOTH required for approved adoption. FUFFLE IS ONLY AVAILABLE FOR ADOPTION WITHIN TWO HOURS OF BIRMINGHAM, ALABAMA BECAUSE A HOME VISIT IS REQUIRED. 

Kerfuffle is located in Alabama and being housed with a foster here. The adoption fee of $150 includes all age appropriate vaccinations, spay/neuter surgery, current flea/tick & heart worm preventative, & microchip. You will also receive a copy of all medical records in a pet health record folder.

Pita & Pecan's Animal Refuge is a veteran owned and operated 501(c)3 nonprofit Alabama based rescue and all of our animals reside with us at our homes or with a foster. We adopt our animals both locally and out-of-state in order to allow us to find the best possible home for our babies of all breeds and species.

PLEASE COMPLETE OUR ADOPTION APPLICATION AT WWW.LOVEBUGSRESCUE.ORG IF YOU'D LIKE TO BE CONSIDERED FOR ONE OF OUR LOVEBUGS:

Bugsy came to Lovebugs Rescue from the Orange Shelter. He is a little old man at 12 years old and weighs just 3 1/2 lbs. Bugsy is very food motivated which has helped transition him into his foster home. He is a little nervous about being touched, but he warms up quickly with some yummy treats. 

Bugsy loves to snuggle up to his special person while watching TV, or going on walks in his sling. He will welcome visitors to the home, and seems to get along fine with other dogs. 

Bugsy has an old luxating patella in one of his back legs, which the hamstring contraction was so severe that he can no longer fully extend the leg and use it. He has been evaluated by our orthopedic and he does just fine using 3 legs. Bugsy also had his last 3 remaining teeth pulled, so he will require a soft food diet. 

Bugsy will do best in a home on the quiet side with someone who is home more often that not. Someone experienced with tiny breeds and who has a love for Chihuahuas would be perfect for him! 

Bugsy's adoption fee is $300 and that includes his neuter, registered microchip, vaccines current, flea treatment and deworming. Applications can be completed at www.lovebugsrescue.org

animal.description:
Medical costs to date: $503.89

Phoebe was originally adopted to a loving home in 2009. Recently, her human mom passed away unexpectedly. Thankfully, animal control did some research and contacted us to once again care for this little girl. Phoebe is approximately 11yo and is in need of donations to help cover her medical expenses, so she can once again be a healthy little Westie girl.

Donations may be made via PayPal to email address:

Donate@scottiekingdom.com

12-4-20: Phoebe only had to spend one night in doggie jail before we rushed to get her out. She is now at our Vet Hospital having tests and to begin treatment for Cushing's Disease. Phoebe has 75% hair loss due to Cushing's Disease.

12-5-20: Phoebe is now in her foster home, receiving medications for Cushing's Disease, as well as dietary supplements to help with her hair loss.

All dogs adopted by Scottie Kingdom Rescue, Inc. have had a full medical exam by one of our licensed Veterinarians, which includes testing (and treatment, if necessary) for Heartworm disease, Lyme disease, Ehrlichia and Anaplasmosis, all necessary vaccinations, spay/neuter surgery, dental cleaning as necessary, microchipping, registration of the microchip, and any other medical needs each particular dog may need. Copies of all available medical records are transferred to you when the adoption is finalized.

We prefer to adopt to families with past Scottie, Westie, Terrier experience, but realize this isn't always possible. We do NOT ship our pets. If you have that special place in your heart, and in your home, for a Scottie (or any of our other available rescue dogs), please visit us in Dallas for an in person meet & greet session with our available dogs. If you have existing dogs, they should travel to Dallas with you, so we can be assured that they will be compatible with the new addition to your family.

Please contact us at
Rescue@scottiekingdom.com
to receive an Adoption Application or for more information on our Adoption process. Also, please take the time to visit our website
www.scottiekingdom.com
for additional information.

We sometimes receive several applications on the same dog. Our goal is to place the dog in the best home possible, based on his/her needs, personality and past history. Please note: Adoptions are not done on a first come, first served basis. Submitting an application does not guarantee the adoption of any dog. We are looking for the best available home for each of our rescue dogs.

Thank you for your understanding, and for considering adoption!

We are
not
supported by your tax dollars or public grants, rather, we rely on donations to help us continue our rescue work for animals that are in need.

Donations may be made via PayPal to email address:

Donate@scottiekingdom.com

or via USPS, to PO Box 551265 ~ Dallas, TX

75355

This pretty pittie is Sydney. She is a 6 year old American Pit Bull Terrier who weighs 48 pounds.

Sydney was adopted from us in 2015 when she was a young pup. She spent over 5 years in what she thought was her forever home, so she's very sad being at the shelter for the first time as an adult. Though she is confused by her circumstances, she lights up when her new human friends at Wish Bone give her love and attention. She is a gentle girl who will sit in your lap and let you pet her all day if you'll let her. Once she gets excited, she does the cutest zoomies. We think Sydney will be very low-key in a home environment - she loves to lay on the couch and is very cuddly. She is fully potty trained.

Sydney attaches to her preferred human and becomes protective over that person. This means that she'll make sure you're always safe, but also means that she should go to a single person household. We aren't sure if a male has treated her unkindly in the past, but she does prefer females. She needs to be the only dog in the house, and does not do well with cats. Sydney will love you with absolutely everything she has and we're excited to find someone who will give her the same in return.

Her minimum adoption fee is $195 plus a $12 fee, if 4 months or older, for rabies registration for McLean County residents.

She has been spayed, microchipped, vaccinated, heartworm checked, dewormed, and is on flea and heartworm preventatives.

For information about this dog's breed(s), visit: http://www.dogbreedinfo.com/abc.htm 

To fill out our adoption application, go to: http://fs16.formsite.com/WishBoneCanineRescue/adoptionapplication/index.html

animal.description:
They say dogs are a mans best friend and Niko is the epitome of that!!! If you are looking for a new best friend, than look no further! Niko loves people and loves to be loved. He would be great on adventures, or a walking/running/jogging buddy or as an integral part of a family - this sweet soul is meant to be a true companion. 

 

He is a Beauty, looks like he is a purebred Husky. His coat is exceptional and his eyes/fade are very striking. He is approximately 2 years of age, and weighs 60 lbs and is neutered, up-to-date on vaccinations, microchipped and heart worm negative. He bonds quickly with humans and loves to play with other dogs. He is very sweet but also protective. Also he is house trained, goes to the door when he wants to go out and knows a few tricks. He is very smart. He needs some help on the leash, as he just wants to chase bunnies and burn some energy. He will wants kisses in the morning and lots of naps, sit on the couch with you or lay by the door taking in the view . He is surprisingly calm in the home for a younger dog and showers each family member equally with affection. Niko is a go anywhere, do anything or just hangout kind of guy - as long as he can share your attention and affection, he is one happy boy!

 

*Homeownership Required!

Adoption fee includes the following:


	Spay/Neuter
	Rabies Vaccination
	Distemper / Parvo Vaccines (includes series of 3 for puppies)
	Bordetella
	Microchip with prepaid lifetime registration
	Deworming

animal.description:
Say hello to Conrad! He is a good boy who is looking for a home to call his own. He is 2 years old, weighs 41 pounds, and we believe he's a black mouth cur mix.

Conrad is energetic, fun-loving, and sweet. He's happiest when he's hanging out with his favorite person and loves to cuddle. He will need plenty of exercise and we've found that he loves puzzle toys and things that keep his mind busy. Conrad would probably do best in a home where someone is home a good deal of the time to play with him and keep him occupied.

He has a high prey drive for cats and we assume he wouldn't do well with other small animals for this reason.  However, based on his interactions with other dogs at the shelter, we think Conrad would be okay in a home with another dog. A dog introduction would be necessary to make sure the dogs get along. Because of his energy level, Conrad requests a home with no children under the age of 6.

His minimum adoption fee is $275 plus a $12 fee, if 4 months or older, for rabies registration for McLean County residents. 

He has been neutered, microchipped, vaccinated, heartworm checked, dewormed, and is on flea and heartworm preventatives.

For information about this dog's breed(s), visit: http://www.dogbreedinfo.com/abc.htm 

To fill out our adoption application, go to: http://fs16.formsite.com/WishBoneCanineRescue/adoptionapplication/index.html

animal.description:
Age: 9-10
Weight: 80
Location: Bucks County, PA
Nicknames: Romey
Good with other dogs?: No, must live as only dog but is safe with other dogs away from home.
He likes smaller dogs.
Good with cats? unknown, will not be adopted to a home with a cat
Good with children? OK for kids over: 10
Activity Preference: Low maintenance overall but needs quality outside time., Champion couch potato, "Energy, do you mean like walking to my food bowl?"
IQ: Smart
Romeo's favorite things: Romeo loves walks with his foster mom and he is perfect on a leash. He loves prancing in the yard as well. He loves everyone he meets.
Romeo is good at: meeting people, staying in a crate, behaving in the house, going for car rides, walking on a leash, cuddling
Ideal home: a fenced yard
Training Needs:
Health issues: Romeo had a mass removed from his testicles when he was neutered.The Vet felt that there were clean margins.

Meet Romeo

Romeo is a rescue from NYC. His mom passed away and her family members brought him to a shelter along with the 2 other dogs he lived with. He is calm, so sweet and so low maintenance. He is so chill but always up for a walk no matter what the distance. His foster mom taught him not to go on the furniture he does not. He is an easy going guy who is the best roomate! He reminds us of Sean Connery!

PLEASE READ: Adopters will not be considered without completing an application. Please visit www.AmericanBulldogRescue.org to apply! Remember - Adoption is always the best option! If you can't help by adopting a homeless pet, please consider making a tax-deductible donation to American Bulldog Rescue, 4 Terry Drive, Suite 1D Newtown, PA 18940 or paypal AmericanBulldogRescue@verizon.net. We cannot place dogs in homes with children under 10 unless that dog has lived with kids or is in a foster home with kids. Thank you.
To be considered for adoption, you must apply using our free, online application. Our dogs are fostered in our volunteers' homes, not in a central shelter/location. Only approved applicants are put into contact with the foster family to setup a meeting with the foster dog. Visit our Adoption Policies web page for more information and a link to our application: http://americanbulldogrescue.org/adoption-policies/.

animal.description:
Hi, my name is Orson. I was transferred to this shelter from another rescue because this shelter was really low on little dogs. I am a very sweet, loving, and affectionate boy, and I love to cuddle and spend time with people. I walk pretty well on the leash and enjoy going out on walks. I can be very picky with other dogs, so if you are interested in adopting me and you have other dogs, we might need to meet a couple times before my adoption is finalized. I haven't really been around cats, but I do bark at them when I see them through the fence. My behaviors with other dogs and cats can definitely be worked with, I will just need someone who understands me, and is willing to work with me. I would love to find a home with a family who will love and cuddle me, and will also exercise me. I really just want to make people happy, and I am very smart, so I will make a wonderful companion for someone. If you have any questions, or if you are interested in adopting me, please ask staff.
                                                                                      Love,
                                                                                     Orson

animal.description:
Hi I'm Zeus and I'm a 1.5 year old, 70lbs Shepherd/Samoyed/Husky mix. 

- Did someone say sweet? I LOVE to be pet and I give the best cuddles.

- I always want to be with you! Separation anxiety is something I'm learning to work through and I will need a patient and understanding individual or family to help me overcome it. My foster mom is helping me LOTS and I promise if we work on it together, we can overcome it!

- Buddy me up! I truly love all dogs, small and big, and would be great in a home with a companion. 

- I am a young energetic boy, who will need to be physically + mentally exercised daily. When you're chill - I'm chill. 

- Adventure Time! I love going on walks, hikes, playing interactive puzzle games for my brain, and being taken around on fun adventures with you! I am great on leash, and even though I'm big, I won't pull you around. 

- I am fully potty trained, and will only go potty outside!

If you see me online I am still available for adoption! If you are interested in adopting me please fill out an application here: www.hitlivingfoundation.org/adoption-application, and email a video walkthrough of your home and yard to BOTH Nicole@hitlivingfoundation.org AND Marta@hitlivingfoundation.org. Your application will not be counted as valid without your video. You will hear back from us within a few days.

animal.description:
Jack-Australian Cattle Dog/mix-male-neutered-10 years-Adoption fee: $100 plus tax.  Update:  Jack's adoption fee has been partially sponsored and will be reduced to $85 + tax with an approved application.   Meet Jack!  This dog is such a sweet older guy.  He came to us when his owner went to the hospital and she could no longer take care of Jack.  Jack is a sweet guy.  He likes to go for walks and at 10 years, he's still ready to go for walks. He is currently in a foster home and he has gone on 5 mile hikes and keeps up.  He's tired afterwards but he doesn't miss a beat. Jack is good with cats and dogs.  He is housetrained too.  Jack is described by his foster mom as "an easy dog to have around."  We think Jack is fabulous and if you would like to offer this guy a permanent home, please apply at www.cchswi.org 

I am fixed, current on my rabies, distemper and kennel cough vaccinations. I am heartworm negative(dogs 6 months and older are tested at CCHS) and started on heartworm prevention. I have been de-wormed and I have also been microchipped. If you are interested in me, please head to the CCHS website at www.cchswi.org and fill out an application. Do you like me but can't adopt me? Consider sponsoring part or all of my adoption fee. This will help me get a home sooner and you can be a part of helping me find a home. You can do this by making a donation through our PayPal donation button on our website. Please note when checking out it's to sponsor my adoption fee. Thank you! DATCP License 266742-DS

animal.description:
Adoption fee on this dog is $100.

Christina is a petite, 10 year old black and tan female weighing just 50 lbs.  She was a stray from a local shelter so we have no history about her past.  Her front teeth are worn and/or broken so a dental procedure is being planned for her and she will require only soft foods in the future. The vet suspects she had been in a kennel or crate quite a bit and she broke her teeth on the metal enclosure.  As might be expected for a senior dog, she has arthritis in her hind end and spondylosis (pinching of the nerves) in her lower spine that affects her stride. Her pain is being managed with anti-inflammatory and nerve blocking meds and they will be required for the remainder of her time. She has some difficulty going up and down 3 steps into and out of the house. Her walks are limited to a quarter to a third of a mile.  She also can slip on hardwood floors unless carpet or runners are put down. 

Christina seems to prefer women over men. In her foster home, she gets fed and walked by the foster dad, but she likes to follow and cuddle with the foster mom and isn’t willing to go to the dad when he calls her.  Initially she retreated to an open crate for security but would come back out for moms attention. Since the crate was removed she has integrated well into her environment and gained confidence around the other dogs. She is living with another larger female German Shepherd and a mid-sized dog in the home who seem to sense she's not feeling her best and leave her alone so they are getting along well. She is housebroken and easy to have around. She uses the dog door but with some difficulty.

Her new home should be a single level home with no steps, with carpet or carpet runners to keep her from slipping.  She also enjoys thick, soft dog beds.  Senior dogs repay kindness with affection and she will be your best friend.

Cats and small critters are unknown.

This dog is a Level 2. Please be sure you understand what a dog of this Level requires. Go to our GCGSR Dogs page for an explanation of the Dog Rating Levels.

For more information and to see when this dog will be attending an Adoption Day, please see our Dogs page on our main website at www.gcgsr.org. 

We operate within a reasonable driving distance from the Greater Sacramento area, the 	Central Valley down to Merced, and Lake Tahoe. A reasonable driving distance is determined by where one of our volunteers is willing to drive within our areas of service. That means we don't adopt out of our area, to Southern California, or Out of State. 

Thank you for visiting!

animal.description:
I am a spunky older gent who acts much much younger. I try really hard to do all the right things, but I would really like it if my family would continue my training. I enjoy other dogs and wouldn't mind sharing my  home with another dog I can play with, but don't much care for dogs who aren't very nice. I would also do best in a home with older kids, small kids just freak me out with all their tantrums. Did I also mention I like walks? I am working on my leash manners but I cannot help enjoying all the great sights and smells outside has to offer. Due to my love for the outdoors, I would really benefit from a tall secure fencing structure in my forever home. I love my people and promise to do the best that I can and show you all the love I have to offer for the rest of my years. 

If you are interested in adopting me please head on over to www.sweethomedobermanrescue.org/application to apply!

animal.description:
This beautiful velvet soft light brown girl is gorgeous. And she winks!!! This amazing girl will stare lovingly in your eyes and then wink. She's been working on getting her girlish figure back and is looking so good! She loves her jogs in the neighborhood and is such a good girl and great companion.

She has her very own 'pink baby'. She walks around all day with it in her mouth .. it is so cute! Bruna does great with other dogs ... her and her foster sister are BFF's ... Bruna would make an amazing buddy for anyone.

Bruna was rescued in the woods after a three day search for her and babies. A volunteer had seen her full of milk and knew she and her babies needed help. She was completely skin and bones but managed to have puppies that were so incredibly healthy. She kept them safe from predators by finding them a safe shelter away from danger. A mother's strength is endless and they will go to the ends of the earth to protect us. That is a true testament to what kind of mother she was. 

Now it's truly her time to get some love. She is a very curious dog and absolutely loves long walks and squirrel chasing ... she is the only dog that I can truly believe she knows exactly what I'm saying . Once you meet her you will understand. She looks at me the entire time I'm talking to her. She is awesome !

All Dallas DogRRR adoptable pets are spayed or neutered, microchipped, and up to date on vaccines upon finalizing adoption. The standard minimum donation for puppies is $325 + 8.25% tax = $351.81, for dogs over 12 months the adoption fee is $225 + 8.25% tax = $243.66 and for our senior dogs 8 years and up is $100 + 8.25% tax = $108.25; this increase includes sales tax recently required by the State of Texas to collect. You can view all the adoptable pets and fill out an adoption application online on our website at http://dallasdogrrr.org. 

For more information, you can email adopt@dallasdogrrr.org. Upon receiving your application please allow us 2-3 business days to review and process.
